ontent/uploads/2013/02/0.gif'),(724,210,'wpcf-types-img-2-cpt','Sensorineural'),(725,210,'wpcf-types-note','<span class=\"crimson\">Diagram:</span> Browse to see the difference between Conductive, Sensorineural, and Mixed hearing loss.'),(726,210,'wpcf-types-main-cntnt','<h3 class=\"crimson\">About conductive hearing loss</h3>\r\n<p>Conductive hearing loss usually results from diseases or disorders that interrupt the sound transmission from the outer and/or middle ear into the inner ear. In cases where the conductive hearing loss is temporary, it is often possible to correct the condition with surgery, medication, or both. In other situations, hearing aids can significantly improve hearing.</p>\r\n<p>Common causes of conductive hearing loss include the following:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Birth defects or deformities</li>\r\n<li>Injury to the outer ear</li>\r\n<li>Ear infections</li>\r\n<li>Head trauma</li>\r\n<li>Blockage of the ear canal</li>\r\n<li>Perforation or stiffening of the ear drum or middle ear bones</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>With conductive hearing loss, the inner ear works properly but something is keeping sound from passing through the outer/middle ear to the inner ear.  A hearing care professional may recommend one of the following, depending on the individual:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Hearing aids (hearing instruments) worn in the ear or behind the ear.  Most modern hearing aids use digital technology to improve speech understanding and sound quality</li>\r\n<li>A surgical solution such as cochlear implants, a bone-anchored hearing appliance (BAHA), or other is not a hearing aid.  It is a surgically attached vibrating transducer attached to the skull using a tiny screw implanted behind the ear</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"crimson\">About sensorineural hearing loss?</h3>\r\n<p>Unlike conductive hearing loss, sensorineural conditions only affect the inner ear or neural pathways. It is the most common type of hearing loss. Sound is transmitted through the outer and middle ears normally but the inner ear is less efficient in transmitting to the brain for processing, usually due to damage to the auditory nerve, the cochlea, and/or hair cells (the fine nerve endings inside the cochlea).</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Sensorineural hearing loss results in reduction of</li>\r\n<li>overall volume</li>\r\n<li>ability to understand speech clearly,</li>\r\n<li>sensitivity to higher frequencies, including soft high-pitched consonants such as <i>s</i>, <i>f</i>, <i>th</i>, and <i>sh</i>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>It also affects the ability to understand high-pitched voices and sounds such as birds singing. Hearing aids are usually a preferred solution for this type of hearing loss.</p>\r\n<p>Sensorineural hearing loss can be <i>congenital</i> (present at birth) or acquired later in life. Common congenital causes include the following:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Hereditary conditions</li>\r\n<li>Viral infections</li>\r\n<li>Premature birth</li>\r\n<li>Injuries resulting in extreme lack of oxygen during birth</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Later-in-life causes may include the following:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Medications with side effects that damage ears</li>\r\n<li>Brain injury</li>\r\n<li>Noise exposure</li>\r\n<li>Aging</li>\r\n<li>Ear infections</li>\r\n<li>Meningitis, encephalitis, or other diseases</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>This audiogram charts the results of someone experiencing sensorineural hearing loss.</p>\r\n<p>Depending upon the specifics of the given case a hearing care professional may recommend:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Hearing aids (hearing instruments) worn in the ear or behind the ear.  Most modern hearing aids use digital technology to improve speech understanding and sound quality</li>\r\n<li>A surgical solution such as cochlear implants, a bone-anchored hearing appliance (BAHA), or other  is not a hearing aid.  It is a surgically attached vibrating transducer attached to the skull using a tiny screw implanted behind the ear</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"crimson\">About mixed hearing loss</h3>\r\n<p><em>Some people have a mix of conductive and sensorineural hearing loss. Treatment options include both medical intervention and hearing aids. </em></p>\r\n<p>This audiogram shows an example of a person experiencing mixed hearing loss.</p>\r\n<p>A hearing care professional will likely consider the following, alone or in combination:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Surgery or surgical implants</li>\r\n<li>Medication</li>\r\n<li>Conventional hearing aids</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Selecting the right method for treatment of a mixed hearing loss depends on the degree of the conductive and sensorineural components. Your hearing care professional will guide you through the process of determining your particular hearing loss treatment options.</p>'),(727,210,'wpcf-section1',''),(728,210,'wpcf-section2',''),(729,210,'wpcf-section3',''),(730,210,'wpcf-types-cta',''),(732,210,'wpcf-types-img-3','http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/0.gif'),(733,210,'wpcf-types-img-3-cpt','Mixed'),(748,229,'_edit_last','1'),(749,229,'_edit_lock','1361234814:1'),(750,159,'_wp_trash_meta_status','draft'),(751,159,'_wp_trash_meta_time','1361234821'),(752,229,'_wp_trash_meta_status','draft'),(753,229,'_wp_trash_meta_time','1361234826'),(754,235,'_wp_types_group_filters_association','any'),(755,235,'_wp_types_group_fields',',sub-hd,types-main-cntnt,'),(756,235,'_wp_types_group_post_types','all'),(757,235,'_wp_types_group_terms','all'),(758,235,'_wp_types_group_templates',',sect1.php,'),(759,235,'_wpcf_conditional_display','a:2:{s:8:\"relation\";s:3:\"AND\";s:6:\"custom\";s:0:\"\";}'),(761,4,'wpcf-sub-hd','About <br/>Hearing Loss'),(764,4,'wpcf-types-main-cntnt','<div class=\"row-fluid\">\r\n<div class=\"span12 sixteen fourpercent main-content bottom-bump\">\r\n<div class=\"span11\">\r\n<p><img class=\"shadowed alignleft\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/how_we_hear.jpg\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></p>\r\n<h3 class=\"crimson thin push-up\">HOW WE HEAR</h3>\r\n<p>Explore the science of hearing, the anatomy of the ear, understand decibels, and learn ten interesting facts about hearing.</p>\r\n<p><a class=\"cta\" href=\"http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/about-hearing-loss/how-we-hear/\">Learn More</a></p>\r\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><img class=\"shadowed alignleft\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/hearing_loss1.jpg\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></p>\r\n<h3 class=\"crimson push-up thin\">HEARING LOSS</h3>\r\n<p>Learn about the signs and symptoms of hearing loss, the different types of hearing loss and what causes each. You can also take an interactive hearing test to see how well your ears work.</p>\r\n<p><a class=\"cta\" href=\"http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/about-hearing-loss/hearing-loss/\">Learn More</a></p>\r\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><img class=\"shadowed alignleft\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/hearing_loss.jpg\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></p>\r\n<h3 class=\"crimson push-up thin\">TINNITUS</h3>\r\n<p>Discover the causes of and treatments for this medical condition that affects 20% of people between 55-65 years of age.</p>\r\n<p><a class=\"cta\" href=\"http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/about-hearing-loss/tinnitus/\">Learn More</a></p>\r\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>To learn how we lose our hearing, view the <a href=\"http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/about-hearing-loss/hearing-loss/causes-of-hearing-loss/\">Causes of Hearing Loss</a> section.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"row-fluid\">\r\n<div class=\"span6\"><a href=\"#CTA1\"><br />\r\n<button class=\"btn btn-large btn-block bottom-bump crimson\" type=\"button\"><i><i><br />\r\n<img class=\"pullright nopad\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/ico_download_20x25.png\" /></i></i> </p>\r\n<p>DOWNLOAD OUR HEARING AID GUIDE </button></a><