ng of what the people in your life who have hearing loss are experiencing, here are ten things you should know about hearing loss:</b></p>'),(3665,160,'wpcf-bttm-content','For more information on possible causes and solutions for hearing loss, contact your personal physician or a hearing care professional. They can help you make good decisions in order to preserve your hearing, test you for any hearing loss, or provide guidance on what to do next if you already know you aren’t hearing things as well as you used to.\r\n\r\n</br></br>'),(3676,969,'wpcf-top-content','<p><b>The following are ten fun facts about hearing:</b></p>'),(3678,969,'wpcf-bttm-content','<p>If you or a family member is struggling with hearing loss, help is available. Contact a hearing care professional today and preserve this life-enriching sense.</p>\r\n<p></br></br></p>'),(3681,579,'_su_rich_snippet_type','none'),(3683,579,'wpcf-top-content','<p><b>Your first fitting is a good opportunity to ask your hearing care professional whatever you want in order to prepare for your new life with hearing aids. Not sure what to ask? We have compiled a list of the top ten questions:</b></p>'),(3685,579,'wpcf-bttm-content','<p>By asking your hearing care professional these and other questions during your fitting, you will increase the likelihood of adapting quickly and successfully to your new hearing aids.</p>'),(3686,12,'_su_rich_snippet_type','none'),(3688,17,'_su_title','Avoiding Hearing Loss | Hearingaids.com'),(3689,17,'_su_description','Hearingaids.com provides suggestions on how to avoid hearing loss.'),(3690,17,'_su_rich_snippet_type','none'),(3692,385,'_su_title','Getting Friends & Family to Accept Treatment | Hearingaids.com'),(3693,385,'_su_description','Hearingaids.com provides guidance on how to detect signs of hearing loss in a family member or friend and then encourage them to seek treatment for their condition.'),(3694,385,'_su_rich_snippet_type','none'),(3696,460,'_su_title','Dealing with Re