INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (1,1,'2013-02-06 22:00:30','2013-02-06 22:00:30','Welcome to WordPress. This is your first post. Edit or delete it, then start blogging!','Hello world!','','publish','open','open','','hello-world','','','2013-02-06 22:00:30','2013-02-06 22:00:30','',0,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com?p=1',0,'post','',1),(2,1,'2013-02-06 22:00:30','2013-02-06 22:00:30','This is an example page. It\'s different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:\n\n<blockquote>Hi there! I\'m a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my blog. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like pi&#241;a coladas. (And gettin\' caught in the rain.)</blockquote>\n\n...or something like this:\n\n<blockquote>The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.</blockquote>\n\nAs a new WordPress user, you should go to <a href=\"http://10.2.10.246/ha.comwp-admin/\">your dashboard</a> to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!','Sample Page','','trash','open','open','','sample-page','','','2013-02-12 22:21:42','2013-02-12 22:21:42','',0,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com?page_id=2',0,'page','',0),(4,1,'2013-02-06 22:05:31','2013-02-07 06:05:31','<p class=\"heading\">This section will explain how we hear and how we lose our hearing. You’ll also learn about tinnitus, the condition where you experience a constant ringing in your ears.</p>\r\n','About Hearing Loss','','publish','open','closed','','about-hearing-loss','','','2013-03-11 11:35:02','2013-03-11 19:35:02','',0,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com?page_id=4',10,'page','',0),(5,1,'2013-02-06 22:05:26','2013-02-06 22:05:26','','About Hearing Loss','','inherit','open','open','','4-revision','','','2013-02-06 22:05:26','2013-02-06 22:05:26','',4,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com?p=5',0,'revision','',0),(6,1,'2013-02-06 22:05:44','2013-02-07 06:05:44','<p class=\"heading\">To understand hearing loss, it helps to know the basic mechanics of how we hear. Our ears, when working properly, are sophisticated organs capable of processing sounds from the scarcely audible to extremely loud. Our ears can assess volume and how close or far away sounds are and identify where sounds originate with a great deal of accuracy. The following explains how this deceptively simple process works.</p>\r\n','How We Hear','','publish','open','closed','','how-we-hear','','','2013-03-08 12:00:07','2013-03-08 20:00:07','',4,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com?page_id=6',10,'page','',0),(7,1,'2013-02-06 22:05:42','2013-02-06 22:05:42','','How We Hear','','inherit','open','open','','6-revision','','','2013-02-06 22:05:42','2013-02-06 22:05:42','',6,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com?p=7',0,'revision','',0),(8,1,'2013-02-06 22:06:02','2013-02-07 06:06:02','<p class=\"heading\">More than 500 million people around the world are experiencing some form of hearing loss right now. Are you one of them?</p>\r\n<p class=\"heading\">If you have hearing loss, you are not alone. About one in six people experience some degree of hearing impairment over the course of their lives.</p>\r\n','Hearing Loss','','publish','open','closed','','hearing-loss','','','2013-03-08 16:32:40','2013-03-09 00:32:40','',4,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com?page_id=8',20,'page','',0),(9,1,'2013-02-06 22:05:58','2013-02-06 22:05:58','','Hearing Loss','','inherit','open','open','','8-revision','','','2013-02-06 22:05:58','2013-02-06 22:05:58','',8,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com?p=9',0,'revision','',0),(10,1,'2013-02-06 22:06:14','2013-02-07 06:06:14','<p class=\"heading\">Tinnitus affects up to 50 million people in the United States<a title=\"\" href=\"#_ftn1\"><sup>[1]</sup></a>. It is the number one disability suffered by combat veterans and affects at least one in every 10 American adults. Yet very few people, even those who have it, know what it is or what they can do to combat it.</p>\r\n<p class=\"heading\">Tinnitus comes from the Latin word <i>tinnire</i> (to ring) and is a perception of sound for which there is no actual external source. You may describe it as ringing in your ears, while to others it sounds like humming, buzzing, or whistling. Tinnitus is a symptom of some kind of damage to your auditory processing system, but is not itself a cause. The most common culprit is the same as for hearing loss — noise exposure. However, sometimes no specific cause can be identified.</p>\r\n','Tinnitus','','publish','open','closed','','tinnitus','','','2013-03-08 16:12:14','2013-03-09 00:12:14','',4,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com?page_id=10',30,'page','',0),(11,1,'2013-02-06 22:06:12','2013-02-06 22:06:12','','Tinnitus','','inherit','open','open','','10-revision','','','2013-02-06 22:06:12','2013-02-06 22:06:12','',10,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com?p=11',0,'revision','',0),(12,1,'2013-02-06 22:07:06','2013-02-07 06:07:06','<p class=\"heading\">In this section, you will the effects of hearing loss on yourself and others, along with how to identify whether you or someone you love has a problem that hearing aids could help.</p>\r\n','Hearing Loss Effects','','publish','open','closed','','hearing-loss-you','','','2013-03-11 11:38:45','2013-03-11 19:38:45','',0,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com?page_id=12',20,'page','',0),(13,1,'2013-02-06 22:07:21','2013-02-06 22:07:21','','Effects of Hearing Loss','','trash','open','open','','effects-of-hearing-loss','','','2013-02-27 16:47:15','2013-02-28 00:47:15','',12,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com?page_id=13',0,'page','',0),(14,1,'2013-02-06 22:07:17','2013-02-06 22:07:17','','Effects of Hearing Loss','','inherit','open','open','','13-revision','','','2013-02-06 22:07:17','2013-02-06 22:07:17','',13,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com13-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(15,1,'2013-02-06 22:08:14','2013-02-06 22:08:14','','Getting Friends & Family to Accept Treatment','','trash','open','open','','getting-friends-family-to-accept-treatment','','','2013-02-22 15:47:42','2013-02-22 23:47:42','',12,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com?page_id=15',0,'page','',0),(16,1,'2013-02-06 22:08:12','2013-02-06 22:08:12','','Getting Friends & Family to Accept Treatment','','inherit','open','open','','15-revision','','','2013-02-06 22:08:12','2013-02-06 22:08:12','',15,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com15-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(17,1,'2013-02-06 22:08:27','2013-02-07 06:08:27','<p class=\"heading\">There is no way around it—the best way to treat any condition is to avoid getting it in the first place. Unfortunately, we often don’t have much control over developing hearing loss. A serious illness, an accident, or the aging process can all cause or contribute to the condition regardless of how careful we are to take preventative measures. However, unlike other sources of hearing loss, noise-induced hearing loss (NIHL) can be prevented if you recognize the risks and take reasonable precautions.</p>\r\n','Avoiding Hearing Loss','','publish','open','closed','','avoiding-hearing-loss','','','2013-03-08 16:41:02','2013-03-09 00:41:02','',12,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com?page_id=17',30,'page','',0),(18,1,'2013-02-06 22:08:25','2013-02-06 22:08:25','','Avoiding Hearing Loss','','inherit','open','open','','17-revision','','','2013-02-06 22:08:25','2013-02-06 22:08:25','',17,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com17-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(19,1,'2013-02-06 22:09:03','2013-02-07 06:09:03','<p class=\"heading\">In this section, you will learn about hearing aids, related accessories and the technology that makes everything work, along with where you can learn more about hearing aids and purchase them.</p>\r\n','Hearing Aids 101','','publish','open','closed','','hearing-aids-101','','','2013-03-11 11:40:44','2013-03-11 19:40:44','',0,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com?page_id=19',30,'page','',0),(20,1,'2013-02-06 22:08:57','2013-02-06 22:08:57','','Hearing Aids 101','','inherit','open','open','','19-revision','','','2013-02-06 22:08:57','2013-02-06 22:08:57','',19,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com19-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(21,1,'2013-02-06 22:09:26','2013-02-06 22:09:26','<p class=\"heading\">Wondering how hearing aids work? The simplest answer is that hearing aids selectively increase the volume of sounds and filter out noises. They make soft sounds more audible and easily understood, while keeping moderate or loud sounds at a comfortable listening level. This helps hearing in both noisy and quiet situations. While no hearing aid can solve every hearing problem or restore normal hearing, today\'s hearing aids adjust to environmental sounds so you can hear and understand better.</p>\r\n','How Hearing Aids Work','','publish','open','open','','how-hearing-aids-work','','','2013-03-07 14:49:16','2013-03-07 22:49:16','',19,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com?page_id=21',10,'page','',0),(22,1,'2013-02-06 22:09:18','2013-02-06 22:09:18','','How Hearing Aids Work','','inherit','open','open','','21-revision','','','2013-02-06 22:09:18','2013-02-06 22:09:18','',21,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com21-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(23,1,'2013-02-06 22:09:48','2013-02-06 22:09:48','','Hearing Aid Buying Guide','','publish','open','open','','hearing-aid-buying-guide','','','2013-03-05 08:05:40','2013-03-05 16:05:40','',19,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com?page_id=23',20,'page','',0),(24,1,'2013-02-06 22:09:42','2013-02-06 22:09:42','','Hearing Aid Buying Guide','','inherit','open','open','','23-revision','','','2013-02-06 22:09:42','2013-02-06 22:09:42','',23,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com23-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(25,1,'2013-02-06 22:10:12','2013-02-06 22:10:12','','Hearing Aids and Audio Equipment','','trash','open','open','','hearing-aids-and-audio-equipment','','','2013-02-28 10:32:59','2013-02-28 18:32:59','',19,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com?page_id=25',30,'page','',0),(26,1,'2013-02-06 22:10:05','2013-02-06 22:10:05','','Hearing Aids and Audio Equipment','','inherit','open','open','','25-revision','','','2013-02-06 22:10:05','2013-02-06 22:10:05','',25,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com25-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(27,1,'2013-02-06 22:10:39','2013-02-07 06:10:39','<p class=\"heading\">In this section, you will learn what to expect throughout the process of purchasing hearing aids, from the initial hearing test through fitting and follow up care.</p>\r\n','Life with Hearing Aids','','publish','open','closed','','life-with-hearing-aids','','','2013-03-11 11:47:22','2013-03-11 19:47:22','',0,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com?page_id=27',40,'page','',0),(28,1,'2013-02-06 22:10:28','2013-02-06 22:10:28','','Life with Hearing Aids','','inherit','open','open','','27-revision','','','2013-02-06 22:10:28','2013-02-06 22:10:28','',27,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com27-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(29,1,'2013-02-06 22:11:09','2013-02-06 22:11:09','','Hearing Aid Fitting','','publish','open','open','','hearing-aid-fitting','','','2013-02-28 10:25:36','2013-02-28 18:25:36','',27,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com?page_id=29',10,'page','',0),(30,1,'2013-02-06 22:10:53','2013-02-06 22:10:53','','Hearing Aid Fitting','','inherit','open','open','','29-revision','','','2013-02-06 22:10:53','2013-02-06 22:10:53','',29,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com29-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(31,1,'2013-02-06 22:12:35','2013-02-06 22:12:35','<p class=\"heading\">Hearing aids have evolved from uncomfortable and unsightly devices to sophisticated, stylish, high-tech instruments with options to compensate for almost every type of hearing impairment. Inconspicuous, yet powerful and versatile, they can do much more than simply make sounds louder.</p>\r\n','The Hearing Aid Experience ','','publish','open','open','','the-hearing-aid-experience','','','2013-03-08 12:17:23','2013-03-08 20:17:23','',27,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com?page_id=31',20,'page','',0),(32,1,'2013-02-06 22:11:21','2013-02-06 22:11:21','','The Hearing Aid Experience ','','inherit','open','open','','31-revision','','','2013-02-06 22:11:21','2013-02-06 22:11:21','',31,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com31-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(33,1,'2013-02-06 22:13:01','2013-02-06 22:13:01','<p>In this series of six videos, you will learn more about using hearing aids and how they improved the lives of actual wearers.</p>','Tutorial and Testimonies','','publish','open','open','','tutorial-and-testimonies','','','2013-03-11 11:48:45','2013-03-11 19:48:45','',27,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com?page_id=33',30,'page','',0),(34,1,'2013-02-06 22:12:54','2013-02-06 22:12:54','','Tutorial and Testimonies','','inherit','open','open','','33-revision','','','2013-02-06 22:12:54','2013-02-06 22:12:54','',33,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com33-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(35,1,'2013-02-06 22:14:27','2013-02-07 06:14:27','','Take Action','','publish','open','closed','','take-action','','','2013-03-11 11:47:46','2013-03-11 19:47:46','',0,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com?page_id=35',50,'page','',0),(36,1,'2013-02-06 22:13:13','2013-02-06 22:13:13','','Take Action','','inherit','open','open','','35-revision','','','2013-02-06 22:13:13','2013-02-06 22:13:13','',35,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com35-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(37,1,'2013-02-06 22:15:34','2013-02-07 06:15:34','If you’ve realized that you or someone you love may be struggling with hearing loss, it’s time to take action. Fill out the form below and a hearing care professional will contact you. Or if you prefer the phone, you can call us at 855-355-9064.','Contact a Hearing Care Professional','','publish','open','closed','','contact-a-hearing-care-provider','','','2013-03-07 07:52:48','2013-03-07 15:52:48','',35,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com?page_id=37',10,'page','',0),(38,1,'2013-02-06 22:15:22','2013-02-06 22:15:22','','Contact a Hearing Care Provider','','inherit','open','open','','37-revision','','','2013-02-06 22:15:22','2013-02-06 22:15:22','',37,'http://10.2.10.246