 is an enriching experience that no one should have to sacrifice.</p>\r\n<p class=\"heading\">You may be concerned that the need to wear hearing aids means an end to your enjoyment of audio entertainment. You’ll be relieved to learn that with today’s modern technology, this is far from true. Hearing aids and accessories are available that allow you to continue to enjoy music in all its forms and from a wide array of media.</p>\r\n','Hearing Aids and Audio Entertainment','','inherit','closed','closed','','770-autosave','','','2013-03-08 12:32:06','2013-03-08 20:32:06','',770,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com770-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(775,3,'2013-02-27 15:50:32','2013-02-27 23:50:32','Audio entertainment is a big part of most peoples’ lives. From portable MP3 players to listening to the band at your local bar to attending a large-venue concert, listening to music is an enriching experience that no one should have to sacrifice.\r\n\r\n<br/><br/>\r\n\r\nYou may be concerned that the need to wear hearing aids means an end to your enjoyment of audio entertainment. You’ll be relieved to learn that with today’s modern technology, this is far from true. Hearing aids and accessories are available that allow you to continue to enjoy music in all its forms and from a wide array of media.','Hearing Aids and Audio Entertainment','','inherit','closed','closed','','770-revision-4','','','2013-02-27 15:50:32','2013-02-27 23:50:32','',770,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com770-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(776,3,'2013-02-26 11:26:58','2013-02-26 19:26:58','There is no way around it—the best way to treat any condition is to avoid getting it in the first place. Unfortunately, we often don’t have much control over developing hearing loss. A serious illness, an accident, or the aging process can all cause or contribute to the condition regardless of how careful we are to take preventative measures. However, unlike other sources of hearing loss, noise-induced hearing loss (NIHL) can be prevented if you recognize the risks and take reasonable precautions.','Avoiding Hearing Loss','','inherit','closed','closed','','17-revision-17','','','2013-02-26 11:26:58','2013-02-26 19:26:58','',17,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com17-revision-17/',0,'revision','',0),(777,3,'2013-02-25 16:13:31','2013-02-26 00:13:31','It is difficult enough to accept hearing loss when it is your own issue. But when it affects a close friend or family member, it can be even more difficult. You may find yourself in the unenviable position of having to convince your parent, grandparent, sibling, or other relative that it is time to get a hearing exam and facing tremendous resistance to the very idea. So how can you convince someone to get tested?','Dealing with Resistance','','inherit','closed','closed','','460-revision-11','','','2013-02-25 16:13:31','2013-02-26 00:13:31','',460,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com460-revision-11/',0,'revision','',0),(778,3,'2013-02-26 11:15:12','2013-02-26 19:15:12','While the downturn in our economy has affected nearly every working-age citizen negatively—either leaving them unable to find a job, change jobs, or receive reasonable cost-of-living salary increases—several studies have shown that those affected by hearing loss have been hit harder than most.','Economic Impact of Hearing Loss','','inherit','closed','closed','','448-revision-14','','','2013-02-26 11:15:12','2013-02-26 19:15:12','',448,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com448-revision-14/',0,'revision','',0),(779,3,'2013-02-06 22:07:21','2013-02-06 22:07:21','','Effects of Hearing Loss','','inherit','closed','closed','','13-revision-2','','','2013-02-06 22:07:21','2013-02-06 22:07:21','',13,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com13-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(780,3,'2013-02-27 12:24:26','2013-02-27 20:24:26','“Loss of hearing is a medical condition that is associated with physical, emotional, mental and social well-being. Depression, anxiety, emotional instability, phobias, withdrawal, isolation, lessened health status and lessened self-esteem have all been linked to uncorrected hearing loss.”<a title=\"\" href=\"#_ftn1\"><b>[1]</b></a>','Getting Friends & Family to Accept Treatment','','inherit','closed','closed','','385-revision-35','','','2013-02-27 12:24:26','2013-02-27 20:24:26','',385,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com385-revision-35/',0,'revision','',0),(781,3,'2013-02-26 12:24:49','2013-02-26 20:24:49','Beyond the emotional impact hearing loss has on you is the toll it takes on others.','Hearing Loss & Others','','inherit','closed','closed','','468-revision-17','','','2013-02-26 12:24:49','2013-02-26 20:24:49','',468,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com468-revision-17/',0,'revision','',0),(782,3,'2013-02-25 14:15:43','2013-02-25 22:15:43','From the moment you were born, you began experiencing your world through your five senses. By seeing, you learned to recognize your father’s smile. By tasting, you learned you preferred peaches to spinach. And by hearing, you were lulled to sleep by your mother’s singing.','Hearing Loss & You','','inherit','closed','closed','','497-revision-9','','','2013-02-25 14:15:43','2013-02-25 22:15:43','',497,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com497-revision-9/',0,'revision','',0),(783,3,'2013-02-26 10:51:50','2013-02-26 18:51:50','Your friend or family member may not be aware he or she is having a problem hearing. In fact, you may not be certain they have a problem, but only suspect something may be going on. By learning to recognize the symptoms associated with hearing loss, you can be more confident when speaking to your friend or family member about your concerns, and be equipped with evidence to back up your claims.','Identifying Hearing Loss in Others Checklist','','inherit','closed','closed','','442-revision-7','','','2013-02-26 10:51:50','2013-02-26 18:51:50','',442,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com442-revision-7/',0,'revision','',0),(784,3,'2013-02-27 15:35:10','2013-02-27 23:35:10','Don’t assume you have all the information you need to make decisions about your hearing—do the rese