sive rate. You may not be aware of all the innovations that have made hearing aids true digital marvels, enabling wearers to hear in all kinds of environments as well as — or sometimes better than — people with natural hearing. Here are ten examples of advances in hearing aid technology to consider when evaluating how hearing aids could enhance the way you experience life.','10 Things You Didn’t Know About Hearing Aid Technology','','inherit','closed','closed','','744-revision-14','','','2013-03-01 15:29:48','2013-03-01 23:29:48','',744,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/744-revision-14/',0,'revision','',0),(1158,3,'2013-02-28 10:26:54','2013-02-28 18:26:54','Your audiogram and your own comments about how well you can hear in a variety of listening environments help determine the optimum setting for your hearing aids. While fitting your hearing aids, your hearing care professional adjusts them by measuring how well you can hear. At your first fitting, you will be taught how to operate your hearing aids and how to hear best in different listening environments. Your hearing care professional will also offer tips for communicating while wearing hearing instruments, encourage you to practice inserting and removing the instruments, and instruct you in cleaning and caring for your hearing aids, as well as proper battery use and storage. You should also expect to schedule an appointment for your first follow up visit about a week later.','10 Things to Ask at Your First Fitting','','inherit','closed','closed','','579-revision-4','','','2013-02-28 10:26:54','2013-02-28 18:26:54','',579,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/579-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(1159,3,'2013-03-01 15:40:16','2013-03-01 23:40:16','Your audiogram and your own comments about how well you can hear in a variety of listening environments help determine the optimum setting for your hearing aids. While fitting your hearing aids, your hearing care professional adjusts them by measuring how well you can hear. At your first fitting, you will be taught how to operate your hearing aids and how to hear best in different listening environments. Your hearing care professional will also offer tips for communicating while wearing hearing instruments, encourage you to practice inserting and removing the instruments, and instruct you in cleaning and caring for your hearing aids, as well as proper battery use and storage. You should also expect to schedule an appointment for your first follow up visit about a week later.\r\n\r\n</br></br>\r\n\r\nText for above facts: Your first fitting is a good opportunity to ask your hearing care professional whatever you want in order to prepare for your new life with hearing aids. Not sure what to ask? We have compiled a list of the top ten questions:\r\n\r\n</br></br>\r\n\r\nText for below facts: By asking your hearing care professional these and other questions during your fitting, you will increase the likelihood of adapting quickly and successfully to your new hearing aids. ','10 Things to Ask at Your First Fitting','','inherit','closed','closed','','579-revision-5','','','2013-03-01 15:40:16','2013-03-01 23:40:16','',579,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/579-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(1160,3,'2013-03-01 15:42:47','2013-03-01 23:42:47','Your audiogram and your own comments about how well you can hear in a variety of listening environments help determine the optimum setting for your hearing aids. While fitting your hearing aids, your hearing care professional adjusts them by measuring how well you can hear. At your first fitting, you will be taught how to operate your hearing aids and how to hear best in different listening environments. Your hearing care professional will also offer tips for communicating while wearing hearing instruments, encourage you to practice inserting and removing the instruments, and instruct you in cleaning and caring for your hearing aids, as well as proper battery use and storage. You should also expect to schedule an appointment for your first follow up visit about a week later.\r\n\r\n</br></br>\r\n\r\nText for above facts: Your first fitting is a good opportunity to ask your hearing care professional whatever you want in order to prepare for your new life with hearing aids. Not sure what to ask? We have compiled a list of the top ten questions:\r\n\r\n</br></br>\r\n\r\nText for below facts: By asking your hearing care professional these and other questions during your fitting, you will increase the likelihood of adapting quickly and successfully to your new hearing aids. ','10 Things to Ask at Your First Fitting','','inherit','closed','closed','','579-revision-6','','','2013-03-01 15:42:47','2013-03-01 23:42:47','',579,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/579-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(1161,3,'2013-02-28 12:19:06','2013-02-28 20:19:06','To understand hearing loss, it helps to know the basic mechanics of how we hear. Our ears, when working properly, are sophisticated organs capable of processing sounds from the scarcely audible to extremely loud. Our ears can assess volume and how close or far away sounds are and identify where sounds originate with a great deal of accuracy. The following explains how this deceptively simple process works.','How We Hear','','inherit','closed','closed','','6-revision-18','','','2013-02-28 12:19:06','2013-02-28 20:19:06','',6,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/6-revision-18/',0,'revision','',0),(1162,3,'2013-02-28 17:42:37','2013-03-01 01:42:37','Do you find yourself asking others to repeat themselves frequently during conversation? Are you straining to understand what the person across the table from you is saying in a crowded restaurant?','Signs & Symptoms Checklist','','inherit','closed','closed','','971-revision-17','','','2013-02-28 17:42:37','2013-03-01 01:42:37','',971,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/971-revision-17/',0,'revision','',0),(1163,3,'2013-03-04 11:11:51','2013-03-04 19:11:51','Do you find yourself asking others to repeat themselves frequently during co