rmine the optimum setting for your hearing aids. While fitting your hearing aids, your hearing care professional adjusts them by measuring how well you can hear. At your first fitting, you will be taught how to operate your hearing aids and how to hear best in different listening environments. Your hearing care professional will also offer tips for communicating while wearing hearing instruments, encourage you to practice inserting and removing the instruments, and instruct you in cleaning and caring for your hearing aids, as well as proper battery use and storage. You should also expect to schedule an appointment for your first follow up visit about a week later.\r\n\r\n</br></br>\r\n\r\nText for above facts: Your first fitting is a good opportunity to ask your hearing care professional whatever you want in order to prepare for your new life with hearing aids. Not sure what to ask? We have compiled a list of the top ten questions:\r\n\r\n</br></br>\r\n\r\nText for below facts: By asking your hearing care professional these and other questions during your fitting, you will increase the likelihood of adapting quickly and successfully to your new hearing aids. ','10 Things to Ask at Your First Fitting','','inherit','closed','closed','','579-revision-7','','','2013-03-01 15:44:29','2013-03-01 23:44:29','',579,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/579-revision-7/',0,'revision','',0),(1201,9,'2013-02-25 14:16:18','2013-02-25 22:16:18','','Hearing Loss & You','','inherit','closed','closed','','12-revision-14','','','2013-02-25 14:16:18','2013-02-25 22:16:18','',12,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/12-revision-14/',0,'revision','',0),(1202,9,'2013-02-27 16:44:37','2013-02-28 00:44:37','There is no way around it—the best way to treat any condition is to avoid getting it in the first place. Unfortunately, we often don’t have much control over developing hearing loss. A serious illness, an accident, or the aging process can all cause or contribute to the condition regardless of how careful we are to take preventative measures. However, unlike other sources of hearing loss, noise-induced hearing loss (NIHL) can be prevented if you recognize the risks and take reasonable precautions.','Avoiding Hearing Loss','','inherit','closed','closed','','17-revision-18','','','2013-02-27 16:44:37','2013-02-28 00:44:37','',17,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/17-revision-18/',0,'revision','',0),(1203,9,'2013-02-27 16:47:34','2013-02-28 00:47:34','“Loss of hearing is a medical condition that is associated with physical, emotional, mental and social well-being. Depression, anxiety, emotional instability, phobias, withdrawal, isolation, lessened health status and lessened self-esteem have all been linked to uncorrected hearing loss.”<a title=\"\" href=\"#_ftn1\"><b>[1]</b></a>','Getting Friends & Family to Accept Treatment','','inherit','closed','closed','','385-revision-36','','','2013-02-27 16:47:34','2013-02-28 00:47:34','',385,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/385-revision-36/',0,'revision','',0),(1204,9,'2013-02-28 10:16:18','2013-02-28 18:16:18','It is difficult enough to accept hearing loss when it is your own issue. But when it affects a close friend or family member, it can be even more difficult. You may find yourself in the unenviable position of having to convince your parent, grandparent, sibling, or other relative that it is time to get a hearing exam and facing tremendous resistance to the very idea. So how can you convince someone to get tested?','Dealing with Resistance','','inherit','closed','closed','','460-revision-13','','','2013-02-28 10:16:18','2013-02-28 18:16:18','',460,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/460-revision-13/',0,'revision','',0),(1205,9,'2013-02-28 10:16:44','2013-02-28 18:16:44','Your friend or family member may not be aware he or she is having a problem hearing. In fact, you may not be certain they have a problem, but only suspect something may be going on. By learning to recognize the symptoms associated with hearing loss, you can be more confident when speaking to your friend or family member about your concerns, and be equipped with evidence to back up your claims.','Identifying Hearing Loss in Others Checklist','','inherit','closed','closed','','442-revision-9','','','2013-02-28 10:16:44','2013-02-28 18:16:44','',442,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/442-revision-9/',0,'revision','',0),(1206,9,'2013-02-28 10:17:36','2013-02-28 18:17:36','Don’t assume you have all the information you need to make decisions about your hearing—do the research, talk to hearing care professionals, and learn to separate the myths from reality. Here are five of the more persistent misconceptions about hearing loss:','Misconceptions about Hearing Loss ','','inherit','closed','closed','','479-revision-26','','','2013-02-28 10:17:36','2013-02-28 18:17:36','',479,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/479-revision-26/',0,'revision','',0),(1207,9,'2013-03-04 11:23:55','2013-03-04 19:23:55','From the moment you were born, you began experiencing your world through your five senses. By seeing, you learned to recognize your father’s smile. By tasting, you learned you preferred peaches to spinach. And by hearing, you were lulled to sleep by your mother’s singing.\r\n\r\n<br/><br/>\r\n\r\nThe reduction or loss of one of your senses has a pronounced effect on your ability to participate in life, and the lives of those you care about. Losing your hearing can be particularly disturbing because it is often associated with aging and ebbing vitality many people are not ready to accept.','Hearing Loss & You','','inherit','closed','closed','','497-revision-12','','','2013-03-04 11:23:55','2013-03-04 19:23:55','',497,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/497-revision-12/',0,'revision','',0),(1208,9,'2013-02-28 10:15:29','2013-02-28 18:15:29','One of the most difficult aspects of hearing loss is the lonely solitude that comes with it. It may prove somewhat comforting to know that not only are you far from alone in experiencing hearing loss, but you share this condition with some very prominent people from the worlds of entertainment, music, sports, and history. Here are just a few inspiring examples.','10 Famous People with Hearing Loss','','inherit','closed','closed','','397-revision-19','','','2013-02-28 10:15:29','2013-02-28 18:15:29','',397,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/397-revision-19/',0,'revision','',0),(1209,9,'2013-02-28 10:14:41','2013-02-28 18:14:41','While the downturn in our economy has affected nearly every working-age citizen negatively—either leaving them unable to find a job, change jobs, or receive reasonable cost-of-living salary increases—several studies have shown that those affected by hearing loss have been hit harder than most.','Economic Impact of Hearing Loss','','inherit','closed','closed','','448-revision-16','','','2013-02-28 10:14:41','2013-02-28 18:14:41','',448,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/448-revision-16/',0,'revision','',0),(1210,9,'2013-02-28 10:15:02','2013-02-28 18:15:02','Beyond the emotional impact hearing loss has on you is the toll it takes on others.','Hearing Loss & Others','','inherit','closed','closed','','468-revision-19','','','2013-02-28 10:15:02','2013-02-28 18:15:02','',468,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/468-revision-19/',0,'revision','',0),(1211,9,'2013-02-27 15:50:50','2013-02-27 23:50:50','Audio entertainment is a big part of most peoples’ lives. From portable MP3 players to listening to the band at your local bar to attending a large-venue concert, listening to music is an enriching experience that no one should have to sacrifice.\r\n\r\n<br/><br/>\r\n\r\nYou may be concerned that the need to wear hearing aids means an end to your enjoyment of audio entertainment. You’ll be relieved to learn that with today’s modern technology, this is far from true. Hearing aids and accessories are available that allow you to continue to enjoy music in all its forms and from a wide array of media.','Hearing Aids and Audio Entertainment','','inherit','closed','closed','','770-revision-5','','','2013-02-27 15:50:50','2013-02-27 23:50:50','',770,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/770-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(1212,9,'2013-02-28 12:16:30','2013-02-28 20:16:30','Wondering how hearing aids work? The simplest answer is that hearing aids selectively increase the volume of sounds and filter out noises. They make soft sounds more audible and easily understood, while keeping moderate or loud sounds at a comfortable listening level. This helps hearing in both noisy and quiet situations. While no hearing aid can solve every hearing problem or restore normal hearing, today\'s hearing aids adjust to environmental sounds so you can hear and understand better.','How Hearing Aids Work','','inherit','closed','closed','','21-revision-18','','','2013-02-28 12:16:30','2013-02-28 20:16:30','',21,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/21-revision-18/',0,'revision','',0),(1213,9,'2013-03-01 15:33:37','2013-03-01 23:33:37','Hearing aid technology continues to evolve at an impressive rate. You may not be aware of all the innovations that have made hearing aids true digital marvels, enabling wearers to hear in all kinds of environments as well as — or sometimes better than — people with natural hearing. Here are ten examples of advances in hearing aid technology to consider when evaluating how hearing aids could enhance the way you experience life.','10 Things You Didn’t Know About Hearing Aid Technology','','inherit','closed','closed','','744-revision-15','','','2013-03-01 15:33:37','2013-03-01 23:33:37','',744,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/744-revision-15/',0,'revision','',0),(1214,9,'2013-03-04 12:45:57','2013-03-04 20:45:57','Hearing aids have come a long way since their inception. The earliest versions from the 19<sup>th</sup> century involved ear trumpets connected to long tubes that directed sound into the ear. Thanks to the efforts of three great inventors, hearing aid technology advanced considerably:\r\n\r\n<br/><br/>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Alexander Graham Bell used a microphone and battery to amplify sound electronically for his new telephone.</li>\r\n	<li>Werner Von Siemens invented the first technology-based solution for hearing loss.</li>\r\n	<li>Thomas Edison invented the carbon transmitter that converted sound into electrical impulses conducted through wires and converted it back again.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<br/>\r\n\r\nHearing aids continued to evolve, using vacuum tubes and then transistors, until entering the modern age of analog, digital, and computers/microchips. Today’s hearing instruments are marvels of technology that continues to advance with each passing year.','Hearing Aid Technology','','inherit','closed','closed','','711-revision-9','','','2013-03-04 12:45:57','2013-03-04 20:45:57','',711,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/711-revision-9/',0,'revision','',0),(1215,9,'2013-02-28 10:19:35','2013-02-28 18:19:35','Hearing aids have come a long way since their invention. Wearers are no longer confined to clunky, obvious beige or grey devices that issue high-pitched whines at the most inconvenient moments. Today’s technology has led to great advances when it comes to function and style options. Several styles of hearing aids are now available, along with many design and color options. The most common types of hearing aids include in-the-ear (ITE) or behind-the-ear (BTE) devices.','Hearing Aid Types','','inherit','closed','closed','','718-revision-6','','','2013-02-28 10:19:35','2013-02-28 18:19:35','',718,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/718-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(1216,9,'2013-02-28 12:34:42','2013-02-28 20:34:42','Today, hearing aids are sophisticated tiny digital sound systems that come in many different styles and with many advanced features. At their core, all hearing instruments are miniature amplification systems made to fit either in the ear or behind the ear. ITE hearing aids have custom formed ear molds made from acrylic or silicon, or an individual shell, while BTE hearing aids come in their own plastic casing, which in some models is interchangeable.\r\n\r\n<br/><br/>\r\n\r\nHearing aids help you enjoy the beauty of sound, but they also reflect your personality and style. You need to be both physically and emotionally comfortable wearing them. The good news is that modern hearing aids are discreet. Some look like fashion accessories, while others are so light and comfortable that if not for your improved hearing, you would forget you were wearing them.','What is a Hearing Aid?','','inherit','closed','closed','','728-revision-8','','','2013-02-28 12:34:42','2013-02-28 20:34:42','',728,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/728-revision-8/',0,'revision','',0),(1217,9,'2013-02-06 22:09:48','2013-02-06 22:09:48','','Hearing Aid Buying Guide','','inherit','closed','closed','','23-revision-2','','','2013-02-06 22:09:48','2013-02-06 22:09:48','',23,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/23-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(1218,9,'2013-02-28 10:24:19','2013-02-28 18:24:19','So many advances have been made in hearing aid technology, it’s no wonder hearing aid wearers are more satisfied with their purchases than ever before. Unfortunately, misconceptions persist about what hearing aids are and what they can do. Don’t let myths keep you from enjoying hearing what you’ve been missing. We’ve dispelled five common misconceptions, so read the facts and rethink putting off that appointment to get your hearing checked.','5 Misconceptions About Hearing Aids ','','inherit','closed','closed','','763-revision-9','','','2013-02-28 10:24:19','2013-02-28 18:24:19','',763,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/763-revision-9/',0,'revision','',0),(1219,9,'2013-02-28 10:23:22','2013-02-28 18:23:22','Before giving an answer to this, it’s important to first clarify the difference between <i>waterproof </i>and <i>water-resistant</i>. While many people use these interchangeably, the reality is they mean very different things. Mistaking <i>–resistant</i> for <i>–proof</i> could cost you a very pricey pair of hearing aids.','Are Hearing Aids Waterproof?','','inherit','closed','closed','','704-revision-7','','','2013-02-28 10:23:22','2013-02-28 18:23:22','',704,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/704-revision-7/',0,'revision','',0),(1220,9,'2013-02-28 10:22:57','2013-02-28 18:22:57','Just like MP3 players and other electronic devices, hearing aids have accessories to keep them clean, functioning optimally, and expand their capabilities. Not sure what’s available or what you need? Here is an overview of several accessories you may want to consider.','Hearing Aid Accessories','','inherit','closed','closed','','691-revision-13','','','2013-02-28 10:22:57','2013-02-28 18:22:57','',691,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/691-revision-13/',0,'revision','',0),(1221,9,'2013-02-28 10:24:05','2013-02-28 18:24:05','Upon the introduction of cell phones, people with hearing loss were faced with yet another challenge — how to take advantage of this popular new technology while wearing hearing instruments? Fortunately, the makers of hearing aids recognized this need and came up with several technological advances to address this challenge.','Hearing Aids and Cell Phones','','inherit','closed','closed','','723-revision-5','','','2013-02-28 10:24:05','2013-02-28 18:24:05','',723,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/723-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(1222,9,'2013-03-05 08:22:11','2013-03-05 16:22:11','Upon the introduction of cell phones, people with hearing loss were faced with yet another challenge — how to take advantage of this popular new technology while wearing hearing instruments? Fortunately, the makers of hearing aids recognized this need and came up with several technological advances to address this challenge.','Hearing Aids and Cell Phones','','inherit','closed','closed','','723-revision-6','','','2013-03-05 08:22:11','2013-03-05 16:22:11','',723,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/723-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(1223,9,'2013-02-28 10:23:51','2013-02-28 18:23:51','Besides hearing aids, there are many devices available to assist you if you are hearing impaired. Thanks to continuing advances in technology intended to make the lives of those with special needs easier, a slew of items are available that can do everything from alert you that your baby is crying to make it easier to listen to a teacher’s presentation in the classroom. The following are just a few innovations of which you should be aware.','Related Products','','inherit','closed','closed','','734-revision-5','','','2013-02-28 10:23:51','2013-02-28 18:23:51','',734,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/734-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(1224,9,'2013-02-28 10:22:20','2013-02-28 18:22:20','Hearing aids are available from most hearing care professionals at their clinics or offices. However, if you are looking for separate providers, we have some other options for you to investigate.','Where to Buy Hearing Aids','','inherit','closed','closed','','739-revision-5','','','2013-02-28 10:22:20','2013-02-28 18:22:20','',739,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/739-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(1225,9,'2013-02-21 18:16:50','2013-02-22 02:16:50','<p class=\"heading\">This section will explain how we hear and how we lose our hearing. You’ll also learn about tinnitus, the condition where you experience a constant ringing in your ears.</p>','About Hearing Loss','','inherit','closed','closed','','4-revision-17','','','2013-02-21 18:16:50','2013-02-22 02:16:50','',4,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/4-revision-17/',0,'revision','',0),(1226,3,'2013-03-08 15:47:26','2013-03-08 23:47:26','<p class=\"heading\">In this section, you will learn about hearing aids, related accessories and the technology that makes everything work, along with where you can learn more about hearing aids and purchase them.</p>\r\n','Hearing Aids 101','','inherit','closed','closed','','19-autosave','','','2013-03-08 15:47:26','2013-03-08 23:47:26','',19,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/19-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(1227,9,'2013-02-21 18:23:48','2013-02-22 02:23:48','','Hearing Aids 101','','inherit','closed','closed','','19-revision-5','','','2013-02-21 18:23:48','2013-02-22 02:23:48','',19,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/19-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(1228,9,'2013-03-05 06:48:43','2013-03-05 14:48:43','','Hearing Loss Effects','','inherit','closed','closed','','12-revision-15','','','2013-03-05 06:48:43','2013-03-05 14:48:43','',12,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/12-revision-15/',0,'revision','',0),(1229,3,'2013-03-08 12:28:51','2013-03-08 20:28:51','<p class=\"heading\">In this section, you will learn what to expect throughout the process of purchasing hearing aids, from the initial hearing test through fitting and follow up care.</p>\r\n','Life with Hearing Aids','','inherit','closed','closed','','27-autosave','','','2013-03-08 12:28:51','2013-03-08 20:28:51','',27,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/27-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(1230,9,'2013-02-06 22:10:39','2013-02-06 22:10:39','','Life with Hearing Aids','','inherit','closed','closed','','27-revision-2','','','2013-02-06 22:10:39','2013-02-06 22:10:39','',27,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/27-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(1231,3,'2013-03-08 16:02:13','2013-03-09 00:02:13','<p>In this section, you will find answers to frequently asked questions about hearing aids.</p>\r\n','FAQs','','inherit','closed','closed','','52-autosave','','','2013-03-08 16:02:13','2013-03-09 00:02:13','',52,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/52-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(1232,9,'2013-02-21 00:47:33','2013-02-21 08:47:33','','FAQ\'s','','inherit','closed','closed','','52-revision-4','','','2013-02-21 00:47:33','2013-02-21 08:47:33','',52,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/52-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(1233,9,'2013-03-04 17:24:20','2013-03-05 01:24:20','Your audiogram and your own comments about how well you can hear in a variety of listening environments help determine the optimum setting for your hearing aids. While fitting your hearing aids, your hearing care professional adjusts them by measuring how well you can hear. At your first fitting, you will be taught how to operate your hearing aids and how to hear best in different listening environments. Your hearing care professional will also offer tips for communicating while wearing hearing instruments, encourage you to practice inserting and removing the instruments, and instruct you in cleaning and caring for your hearing aids, as well as proper battery use and storage. You should also expect to schedule an appointment for your first follow up visit about a week later.','10 Things to Ask at Your First Fitting','','inherit','closed','closed','','579-revision-8','','','2013-03-04 17:24:20','2013-03-05 01:24:20','',579,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/579-revision-8/',0,'revision','',0),(1234,9,'2013-02-28 10:26:17','2013-02-28 18:26:17','If you have already scheduled an appointment for your first hearing aid fitting, you are probably wondering what information you should know or bring with you. The more thorough background about your medical history, hearing issues, lifestyle, and other unique needs you can provide, the easier it will be for the hearing aid provider to help you choose and be fitted for the best possible hearing instruments.','Appointment Checklist','','inherit','closed','closed','','597-revision-11','','','2013-02-28 10:26:17','2013-02-28 18:26:17','',597,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/597-revision-11/',0,'revision','',0),(1235,9,'2013-03-04 13:16:44','2013-03-04 21:16:44','Learning to listen with hearing aids takes time and a degree of patience in the beginning. It‘s also important to be realistic and not to expect 100 percent flawless hearing in every situation, especially right away. The key to success is forming an active partnership with your provider, reading all materials provided, and following directions.\r\n<br/><br/>\r\nDuring follow up visits, your hearing aid provider will answer any questions that may arise with use, make any technical adjustments or cleaning warranted, and generally help you adapt to and enjoy your hearing instruments. Here is what to expect during these follow up visits.','Follow-Up Visits and Warranties','','inherit','closed','closed','','583-revision-18','','','2013-03-04 13:16:44','2013-03-04 21:16:44','',583,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/583-revision-18/',0,'revision','',0),(1236,9,'2013-03-04 13:11:39','2013-03-04 21:11:39','You’ve met with a hearing care professional, had your audiogram, learned which hearing aids will work best for you, and made the decision to move forward. Congratulations! Now it’s time to prepare for your hearing aid fitting. To help alleviate any anxiety you may be feeling, here is what you should expect to go on during this important visit.','What to Expect at Your First Fitting','','inherit','closed','closed','','633-revision-11','','','2013-03-04 13:11:39','2013-03-04 21:11:39','',633,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/633-revision-11/',0,'revision','',0),(1237,9,'2013-03-04 13:18:20','2013-03-04 21:18:20','Hearing aids have evolved from uncomfortable and unsightly devices to sophisticated, stylish, high-tech instruments with options to compensate for almost every type of hearing impairment. Inconspicuous, yet powerful and versatile, they can do much more than simply make sounds louder.','The Hearing Aid Experience ','','inherit','closed','closed','','31-revision-12','','','2013-03-04 13:18:20','2013-03-04 21:18:20','',31,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/31-revision-12/',0,'revision','',0),(1238,9,'2013-02-28 10:28:19','2013-02-28 18:28:19','Let’s say you already met with a hearing care professional and determined that hearing aids are right for you. Now you face an array of choices about the type of hearing instruments available. From behind-the-ear (BTE) to in-the-ear (ITE) models, you may be overwhelmed by how many choices you have and unsure which version will suit your lifestyle.','Lifestyle Inventory Checklist','','inherit','closed','closed','','619-revision-14','','','2013-02-28 10:28:19','2013-02-28 18:28:19','',619,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/619-revision-14/',0,'revision','',0),(1239,9,'2013-03-04 13:23:48','2013-03-04 21:23:48','Most digital hearing aids are equipped with options to allow you to hear in a variety of environments. As you change settings throughout the day, you can push a button on your hearing aids to select a program appropriate to your surroundings. Or, if you have more advanced digital hearing aids, they will switch programs automatically based on an analysis of environmental sounds. Your audiologist or other hearing care professional will set up the programs at your fitting and tweak them as necessary during follow-up visits.','Settings for Different Environments','','inherit','closed','closed','','642-revision-7','','','2013-03-04 13:23:48','2013-03-04 21:23:48','',642,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/642-revision-7/',0,'revision','',0),(1240,9,'2013-03-04 13:23:30','2013-03-04 21:23:30','Hearing aids have improved the travel experience for numerous hearing impaired tourists. Instead of straining to hear tour guides, missing boarding announcements, and struggling to negotiate unfamiliar public transportation, hearing aid wearers can enjoy trips without extra hassle and worry. But, it’s important to protect and maintain your hearing aids while traveling, so that they continue to provide the top performance you need while away from home.','Traveling with Hearing Aids','','inherit','closed','closed','','648-revision-8','','','2013-03-04 13:23:30','2013-03-04 21:23:30','',648,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/648-revision-8/',0,'revision','',0),(1241,9,'2013-02-26 11:41:57','2013-02-26 19:41:57','','Glossary','','inherit','closed','closed','','54-revision-9','','','2013-02-26 11:41:57','2013-02-26 19:41:57','',54,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/54-revision-9/',0,'revision','',0),(1242,9,'2013-02-27 17:03:41','2013-02-28 01:03:41','If you are ready to find out whether you should get hearing aids or not, you may be wondering, “Where do I find a hearing care professional?” The good news is there are many options available. You should take care to choose one who is readily available, reliable, trustworthy, and offers the most services for your money.','Where to Find a Hearing Care Provider','','inherit','closed','closed','','58-revision-19','','','2013-02-27 17:03:41','2013-02-28 01:03:41','',58,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/58-revision-19/',0,'revision','',0),(1243,9,'2013-02-27 17:20:57','2013-02-28 01:20:57','Here are answers to some of the most commonly asked questions about hearing loss and hearing aids. For answers specific to your concerns, consult a hearing care professional for proper examination and testing.','FAQs','','inherit','closed','closed','','60-revision-22','','','2013-02-27 17:20:57','2013-02-28 01:20:57','',60,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/60-revision-22/',0,'revision','',0),(1244,9,'2013-03-05 08:51:28','2013-03-05 16:51:28','In this section, you will find answers to frequently asked questions about hearing aids.','FAQs','','inherit','closed','closed','','52-revision-5','','','2013-03-05 08:51:28','2013-03-05 16:51:28','',52,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/52-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(1245,3,'2013-03-04 17:22:33','2013-03-05 01:22:33','How you hear naturally is fascinating. Think about it.  All of the components of this intricately designed process must work at peak function to carry waves in the air around you to your brain, where they are understood as distinct sounds. Hearing allows you to communicate, learn, experience, and enjoy the world around you.','10 Cool Facts about Hearing','','inherit','closed','closed','','969-revision-16','','','2013-03-04 17:22:33','2013-03-05 01:22:33','',969,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/969-revision-16/',0,'revision','',0),(1246,3,'2013-03-05 13:33:03','2013-03-05 21:33:03','How you hear naturally is fascinating. Think about it.  All of the components of this intricately designed process must work at peak function to carry waves in the air around you to your brain, where they are understood as distinct sounds. Hearing allows you to communicate, learn, experience, and enjoy the world around you.','10 Cool Facts about Hearing','','inherit','closed','closed','','969-revision-17','','','2013-03-05 13:33:03','2013-03-05 21:33:03','',969,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/969-revision-17/',0,'revision','',0),(1248,3,'2013-03-05 08:10:04','2013-03-05 16:10:04','Before giving an answer to this, it’s important to first clarify the difference between <i>waterproof </i>and <i>water-resistant</i>. While many people use these interchangeably, the reality is they mean very different things. Mistaking <i>–resistant</i> for <i>–proof</i> could cost you a very pricey pair of hearing aids.','Are Hearing Aids Waterproof?','','inherit','closed','closed','','704-revision-8','','','2013-03-05 08:10:04','2013-03-05 16:10:04','',704,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/704-revision-8/',0,'revision','',0),(1249,3,'2013-03-05 14:20:44','2013-03-05 22:20:44','Before giving an answer to this, it’s important to first clarify the difference between <i>waterproof </i>and <i>water-resistant</i>. While many people use these interchangeably, the reality is they mean very different things. Mistaking <i>–resistant</i> for <i>–proof</i> could cost you a very pricey pair of hearing aids.','Are Hearing Aids Waterproof?','','inherit','closed','closed','','704-revision-9','','','2013-03-05 14:20:44','2013-03-05 22:20:44','',704,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/704-revision-9/',0,'revision','',0),(1250,1,'2013-03-05 08:33:32','2013-03-05 16:33:32','<p class=\"heading\">This section will explain how we hear and how we lose our hearing. You’ll also learn about tinnitus, the condition where you experience a constant ringing in your ears.</p>','About Hearing Loss','','inherit','closed','closed','','4-revision-18','','','2013-03-05 08:33:32','2013-03-05 16:33:32','',4,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/4-revision-18/',0,'revision','',0),(1251,3,'2013-03-06 11:28:16','2013-03-06 19:28:16','','Terms of Use','','publish','closed','closed','','terms','','','2013-03-06 18:03:14','2013-03-07 02:03:14','',114,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/?