on','',0),(1268,3,'2013-03-06 17:36:00','2013-03-07 01:36:00','','Privacy Policy & Disclaimers','','inherit','closed','closed','','1264-autosave','','','2013-03-06 17:36:00','2013-03-07 01:36:00','',1264,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/1264-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(1269,3,'2013-03-06 12:51:19','2013-03-06 20:51:19','','Privacy Policy & Disclaimers','','inherit','closed','closed','','1264-revision-4','','','2013-03-06 12:51:19','2013-03-06 20:51:19','',1264,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/1264-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(1270,3,'2013-03-06 16:25:06','2013-03-07 00:25:06','<p>Hearing loss can make you feel isolated, but you are not alone. Check out these short videos from real people just like you who confronted their hearing loss.</p>','Personal Stories about Hearing Loss','','publish','closed','closed','','personal-stories-hearing-loss','','','2013-03-11 11:12:56','2013-03-11 19:12:56','',497,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/?page_id=1270',30,'page','',0),(1271,3,'2013-03-06 16:25:01','2013-03-07 00:25:01','','Personal Stories about Hearing Loss','','inherit','closed','closed','','1270-revision','','','2013-03-06 16:25:01','2013-03-07 00:25:01','',1270,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/1270-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(1272,3,'2013-03-06 16:27:16','2013-03-07 00:27:16','<p>Reluctant to address your hearing loss? Have a loved one who is afraid to confront theirs? Watch this real-life testimonial from a daughter whose mom was initially resistant to seeking treatment, but was ultimately very happy that she did.</p>','Hearing is Believing','','publish','closed','closed','','hearing-believing','','','2013-03-11 11:37:25','2013-03-11 19:37:25','',385,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/?page_id=1272',20,'page','',0),(1273,3,'2013-03-06 16:26:57','2013-03-07 00:26:57','','Hearing is Believing','','inherit','closed','closed','','1272-revision','','','2013-03-06 16:26:57','2013-03-07 00:26:57','',1272,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/1272-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(1274,3,'2013-03-06 16:28:16','2013-03-07 00:28:16','','Hearing Loss Simulator','','publish','closed','closed','','hearing-loss-simulator','','','2013-03-06 17:05:11','2013-03-07 01:05:11','',385,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/?page_id=1274',40,'page','',0),(1275,3,'2013-03-06 16:28:00','2013-03-07 00:28:00','','Hearing Loss Simulator','','inherit','closed','closed','','1274-revision','','','2013-03-06 16:28:00','2013-03-07 00:28:00','',1274,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/1274-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(1276,3,'2013-03-06 16:28:16','2013-03-07 00:28:16','','Hearing Loss Simulator','','inherit','closed','closed','','1274-revision-2','','','2013-03-06 16:28:16','2013-03-07 00:28:16','',1274,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/1274-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(1277,3,'2013-03-06 16:31:54','2013-03-07 00:31:54','<p>Wondering how to get a friend or loved one to seek treatment for their hearing loss? An audiologist suggests what steps to take in this video.</p>','First Steps Toward a Solution','','publish','closed','closed','','steps-solution','','','2013-03-11 11:42:15','2013-03-11 19:42:15','',385,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/?page_id=1277',50,'page','',0),(1278,3,'2013-03-06 16:31:41','2013-03-07 00:31:41','','First Steps Toward a Solution','','inherit','closed','closed','','1277-revision','','','2013-03-06 16:31:41','2013-03-07 00:31:41','',1277,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/1277-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(1279,3,'2013-02-28 16:41:31','2013-03-01 00:41:31','More than 500 million people around the world are experiencing some form of hearing loss right now. Are you one of them?\r\n\r\n<br/><br/>\r\n\r\nIf you have hearing loss, you are not alone. About one in six people experience some degree of hearing impairment over the course of their lives.','Hearing Loss','','inherit','closed','closed','','8-revision-10','','','2013-02-28 16:41:31','2013-03-01 00:41:31','',8,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/8-revision-10/',0,'revision','',0),(1280,3,'2013-03-04 17:17:37','2013-03-05 01:17:37','Researchers continue to learn more about hearing loss, its causes and contributing factors, and effects. There are ways to reduce the likelihood of losing your hearing in some cases, while others are simply beyond our control.\r\n','10 Things to Know about Hearing Loss','','inherit','closed','closed','','160-revision-29','','','2013-03-04 17:17:37','2013-03-05 01:17:37','',160,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/160-revision-29/',0,'revision','',0),(1281,3,'2013-03-04 13:57:20','2013-03-04 21:57:20','If you already read our types of hearing loss overview, you know that there are several types of hearing loss. There are also many causes.','Causes of Hearing Loss','','inherit','closed','closed','','975-revision-7','','','2013-03-04 13:57:20','2013-03-04 21:57:20','',975,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/975-revision-7/',0,'revision','',0),(1282,3,'2013-03-04 13:58:41','2013-03-04 21:58:41','[slickquiz id=1]','Interactive Hearing Test','','inherit','closed','closed','','179-revision-27','','','2013-03-04 13:58:41','2013-03-04 21:58:41','',179,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/179-revision-27/',0,'revision','',0),(1283,3,'2013-03-04 14:01:05','2013-03-04 22:01:05','Hearing loss is often a symptom or outcome of other medical conditions, which can be very serious or even life threatening. This is yet another reason that it is so important to recognize the signs of hearing loss and seek treatment from a hearing care professional as soon as possible. More than your hearing may be at stake.\r\n\r\nThe following are a sampling of other illnesses and afflictions linked to hearing loss. A qualified otolaryngologist (ear, nose, and throat doctor or ENT) or certified audiologist can help diagnose these conditions and provide recommendations for treatment.','Related Medical Conditions','','inherit','closed','closed','','976-revision-9','','','2013-03-04 14:01:05','2013-03-04 22:01:05','',976,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/976-revision-9/',0,'revision','',0),(1284,3,'2013-03-04 14:03:33','2013-03-04 22:03:33','Do you find yourself asking others to repeat themselves frequently during conversation? Are you straining to understand what the person across the table from you is saying in a crowded restaurant?\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThese are just two of the indicators that you may have hearing loss. The following checklist can help you figure out if you might benefit from seeing a hearing care professional. If you answer “yes” to one or more of these, you should schedule an appointment as soon as possible. The sooner you seek treatment for hearing loss, the more of your remaining hearing can be protected.','Signs & Symptoms Checklist','','inherit','closed','closed','','971-revision-21','','','2013-03-04 14:03:33','2013-03-04 22:03:33','',971,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/971-revision-21/',0,'revision','',0),(1285,3,'2013-03-04 14:07:01','2013-03-04 22:07:01','When you see a hearing care professional for diagnosis of your hearing loss, he or she is likely to tell you more than simply, “You have lost some hearing.” Rather, you will probably be told that you have a specific type of hearing loss:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>conductive</li>\r\n	<li>sensorineural</li>\r\n	<li>mixed</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nHere’s a brief overview of each hearing loss type, its likely causes, and the treatment options usually proposed.','Types of Hearing Loss','','inherit','closed','closed','','210-revision-25','','','2013-03-04 14:07:01','2013-03-04 22:07:01','',210,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/210-revision-25/',0,'revision','',0),(1286,3,'2013-03-04 14:11:24','2013-03-04 22:11:24','To understand hearing loss, it helps to know the basic mechanics of how we hear. Our ears, when working properly, are sophisticated organs capable of processing sounds from the scarcely audible to extremely loud. Our ears can assess volume and how close or far away sounds are and identify where sounds originate with a great deal of accuracy. The following explains how this deceptively simple process works.','How We Hear','','inherit','closed','closed','','6-revision-20','','','2013-03-04 14:11:24','2013-03-04 22:11:24','',6,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/6-revision-20/',0,'revision','',0),(1287,3,'2013-03-05 13:33:21','2013-03-05 21:33:21','How you hear naturally is fascinating. Think about it.  All of the components of this intricately designed process must work at peak function to carry waves in the air around you to your brain, where they are understood as distinct sounds. Hearing allows you to communicate, learn, experience, and enjoy the world around you.','10 Cool Facts about Hearing','','inherit','closed','closed','','969-revision-18','','','2013-03-05 13:33:21','2013-03-05 21:33:21','',969,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/969-revision-18/',0,'revision','',0),(1288,3,'2013-03-04 17:14:58','2013-03-05 01:14:58','Your ears can be damaged if you are overexposed to excessive noise—either one-time exposure to an extremely loud sound (e.g., an explosion) or regular exposure over time (e.g., heavy machinery on the job). This is called <i>noise-induced hearing loss</i> (NIHL). Once you lose vital structures like the hair cells that send sound impulses to your brain, they cannot be repaired. So, how do you know what is just loud versus sound levels that are dangerous to your hearing?\r\n\r\nThe loudness of sound is measurable, using units called <i>decibels</i> (dB). A decibel unit expresses the relative intensity of sounds on a scale from zero (think a gentle breeze) to about 120 dB (think fireworks). Normal speech is typically between 50 to 60 dB.','What are Decibels?','','inherit','closed','closed','','967-revision-19','','','2013-03-04 17:14:58','2013-03-05 01:14:58','',967,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/967-revision-19/',0,'revision','',0),(1289,3,'2013-03-06 16:52:58','2013-03-07 00:52:58','Your ears can be damaged if you are overexposed to excessive noise—either one-time exposure to an extremely loud sound (e.g., an explosion) or regular exposure over time (e.g., heavy machinery on the job). This is called <i>noise-induced hearing loss</i> (NIHL). Once you lose vital structures like the hair cells that send sound impulses to your brain, they cannot be repaired. So, how do you know what is just loud versus sound levels that are dangerous to your hearing?\r\n\r\nThe loudness of sound is measurable, using units called <i>decibels</i> (dB). A decibel unit expresses the relative intensity of sounds on a scale from zero (think a gentle breeze) to about 120 dB (think fireworks). Normal speech is typically between 50 to 60 dB.','What are Decibels?','','inherit','closed','closed','','967-revision-20','','','2013-03-06 16:52:58','2013-03-07 00:52:58','',967,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/967-revision-20/',0,'revision','',0),(1290,3,'2013-03-06 12:04:05','2013-03-06 20:04:05','[slickquiz id=2]','How Do We Hear Quiz','','inherit','closed','closed','','966-revision-5','','','2013-03-06 12:04:05','2013-03-06 20:04:05','',966,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/966-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(1291,3,'2013-03-04 14:16:58','2013-03-04 22:16:58','<a href=\"http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/Anatomy-of-the-Ear.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-1017\" alt=\"Anatomy of the Ear\" src=\"http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/Anatomy-of-the-Ear.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"296\" /></a>','Anatomy of the Ear','','inherit','closed','closed','','964-revision-6','','','2013-03-04 14:16:58','2013-03-04 22:16:58','',964,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/964-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(1292,3,'2013-03-04 14:23:42','2013-03-04 22:23:42','Tinnitus affects up to 50 million people in the United States<a title=\"\" href=\"#_ftn1\">[1]</a>. It is the number one disability suffered by combat veterans and affects at least one in every 10 American adults. Yet very few people, even those who have it, know what it is or what they can do to combat it.\r\n\r\nTinnitus comes from the Latin word <i>tinnire</i> (to ring) and is a perception of sound for which there is no actual external source. You may describe it as ringing in your ears, while to others it sounds like humming, buzzing, or whistling. Tinnitus is a symptom of some kind of damage to your auditory processing system, but is not itself a cause. The most common culprit is the same as for hearing loss — noise exposure. However, sometimes no specific cause can be identified.\r\n<div><br clear=\"all\" />\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"left\" size=\"1\" width=\"33%\" />\r\n\r\n</div>','Tinnitus','','inherit','closed','closed','','10-revision-12','','','2013-03-04 14:23:42','2013-03-04 22:23:42','',10,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/10-revision-12/',0,'revision','',0),(1293,3,'2013-03-05 07:34:05','2013-03-05 15:34:05','Audio entertainment is a big part of most peoples’ lives. From portable MP3 players to listening to the band at your local bar to attending a large-venue concert, listening to music is an enriching experience that no one should have to sacrifice.\r\n\r\nYou may be concerned that the need to wear hearing aids means an end to your enjoyment of audio entertainment. You’ll be relieved to learn that with today’s modern technology, this is far from true. Hearing aids and accessories are available that allow you to continue to enjoy music in all its forms and from a wide array of media.','Hearing Aids and Audio Entertainment','','inherit','closed','closed','','770-revision-6','','','2013-03-05 07:34:05','2013-03-05 15:34:05','',770,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/770-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(1294,3,'2013-03-05 07:37:29','2013-03-05 15:37:29','Hearing aid technology continues to evolve at an impressive rate. You may not be aware of all the innovations that have made hearing aids true digital marvels, enabling wearers to hear in all kinds of environments as well as — or sometimes better than — people with natural hearing. Here are ten examples of advances in hearing aid technology to consider when evaluating how hearing aids could enhance the way you experience life.','10 Things You Didn’t Know About Hearing Aid Technology','','inherit','closed','closed','','744-revision-16','','','2013-03-05 07:37:29','2013-03-05 15:37:29','',744,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/744-revision-16/',0,'revision','',0),(1295,3,'2013-03-05 07:42:47','2013-03-05 15:42:47','Hearing aids have come a long way since their inception. The earliest versions from the 19<sup>th</sup> century involved ear trumpets connected to long tubes that directed sound into the ear. Thanks to the efforts of three great inventors, hearing aid technology advanced considerably:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Alexander Graham Bell used a microphone and battery to amplify sound electronically for his new telephone.</li>\r\n	<li>Werner Von Siemens invented the first technology-based solution for hearing loss.</li>\r\n	<li>Thomas Edison invented the carbon transmitter that converted sound into electrical impulses conducted through wires and converted it back again.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHearing aids continued to evolve, using vacuum tubes and then transistors, until entering the modern age of analog, digital, and computers/microchips. Today’s hearing instruments are marvels of technology that continues to advance with each passing year.','Hearing Aid Technology','','inherit','closed','closed','','711-revision-10','','','2013-03-05 07:42:47','2013-03-05 15:42:47','',711,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/711-revision-10/',0,'revision','',0),(1296,3,'2013-03-05 07:44:06','2013-03-05 15:44:06','Hearing aids have come a long way since their invention. Wearers are no longer confined to clunky, obvious beige or grey devices that issue high-pitched whines at the most inconvenient moments. Today’s technology has led to great advances when it comes to function and style options. Several styles of hearing aids are now available, along with many design and color options. The most common types of hearing aids include in-the-ear (ITE) or behind-the-ear (BTE) devices.','Hearing Aid Types','','inherit','closed','closed','','718-revision-7','','','2013-03-05 07:44:06','2013-03-05 15:44:06','',718,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/718-revision-7/',0,'revision','',0),(1297,3,'2013-03-05 08:04:21','2013-03-05 16:04:21','Today, hearing aids are sophisticated tiny digital sound systems that come in many different styles and with many advanced features. At their core, all hearing instruments are miniature amplification systems made to fit either in the ear or behind the ear. ITE hearing aids have custom formed ear molds made from acrylic or silicon, or an individual shell, while BTE hearing aids come in their own plastic casing, which in some models is interchangeable.\r\n\r\nHearing aids help you enjoy the beauty of sound, but they also reflect your personality and style. You need to be both physically and emotionally comfortable wearing them. The good news is that modern hearing aids are discreet. Some look like fashion accessories, while others are so light and comfortable that if not for your improved hearing, you would forget you were wearing them.','What is a Hearing Aid?','','inherit','closed','closed','','728-revision-9','','','2013-03-05 08:04:21','2013-03-05 16:04:21','',728,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/728-revision-9/',0,'revision','',0),(1298,3,'2013-03-05 08:26:32','2013-03-05 16:26:32','Hearing aids are available from most hearing care professionals at their clinics or offices. However, if you are looking for separate providers, we have some other options for you to investigate.','Where to Buy Hearing Aids','','inherit','closed','closed','','739-revision-6','','','2013-03-05 08:26:32','2013-03-05 16:26:32','',739,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/739-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(1299,3,'2013-03-05 08:20:36','2013-03-05 16:20:36','Just like MP3 players and other electronic devices, hearing aids have accessories to keep them clean, functioning optimally, and expand their capabilities. Not sure what’s available or what you need? Here is an overview of several accessories you may want to consider.','Hearing Aid Accessories','','inherit','closed','closed','','691-revision-14','','','2013-03-05 08:20:36','2013-03-05 16:20:36','',691,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/691-revision-14/',0,'revision','',0),(1300,3,'2013-03-05 14:21:13','2013-03-05 22:21:13','Before giving an answer to this, it’s important to first clarify the difference between <i>waterproof </i>and <i>water-resistant</i>. While many people use these interchangeably, the reality is they mean very different things. Mistaking <i>–resistant</i> for <i>–proof</i> could cost you a very pricey pair of hearing aids.','Are Hearing Aids Waterproof?','','inherit','closed','closed','','704-revision-10','','','2013-03-05 14:21:13','2013-03-05 22:21:13','',704,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/704-revision-10/',0,'revision','',0),(1301,3,'2013-03-05 08:25:12','2013-03-05 16:25:12','Besides hearing aids, there are many devices available to assist you if you are hearing impaired. Thanks to continuing advances in technology intended to make the lives of those with special needs easier, a slew of items are available that can do everything from alert you that your baby is crying to make it easier to listen to a teacher’s presentation in the classroom. The following are just a few innovations of which you should be aware.','Related Products','','inherit','closed','closed','','734-revision-6','','','2013-03-05 08:25:12','2013-03-05 16:25:12','',734,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/734-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(1302,3,'2013-03-05 08:22:37','2013-03-05 16:22:37','Upon the introduction of cell phones, people with hearing loss were faced with yet another challenge — how to take advantage of this popular new technology while wearing hearing instruments? Fortunately, the makers of hearing aids recognized this need and came up with several technological advances to address this challenge.','Hearing Aids and Cell Phones','','inherit','closed','closed','','723-revision-7','','','2013-03-05 08:22:37','2013-03-05 16:22:37','',723,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/723-revision-7/',0,'revision','',0),(1303,3,'2013-03-05 08:06:53','2013-03-05 16:06:53','So many advances have been made in hearing aid technology, it’s no wonder hearing aid wearers are more satisfied with their purchases than ever before. Unfortunately, misconceptions persist about what hearing aids are and what they can do. Don’t let myths keep you from enjoying hearing what you’ve been missing. We’ve dispelled five common misconceptions, so read the facts and rethink putting off that appointment to get your hearing checked.','5 Misconceptions About Hearing Aids ','','inherit','closed','closed','','763-revision-10','','','2013-03-05 08:06:53','2013-03-05 16:06:53','',763,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/763-revision-10/',0,'revision','',0),(1304,3,'2013-03-05 06:52:37','2013-03-05 14:52:37','There is no way around it—the best way to treat any condition is to avoid getting it in the first place. Unfortunately, we often don’t have much control over developing hearing loss. A serious illness, an accident, or the aging process can all cause or contribute to the condition regardless of how careful we are to take preventative measures. However, unlike other sources of hearing loss, noise-induced hearing loss (NIHL) can be prevented if you recognize the risks and take reasonable precautions.','Avoiding Hearing Loss','','inherit','closed','closed','','17-revision-19','','','2013-03-05 06:52:37','2013-03-05 14:52:37','',17,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/17-revision-19/',0,'revision','',0),(1305,3,'2013-03-05 06:54:59','2013-03-05 14:54:59','“Loss of hearing is a medical condition that is associated with physical, emotional, mental and social well-being. Depression, anxiety, emotional instability, phobias, withdrawal, isolation, lessened health status and lessened self-esteem have all been linked to uncorrected hearing loss.”<a title=\"\" href=\"#_ftn1\"><b>[1]</b></a>','Getting Friends & Family to Accept Treatment','','inherit','closed','closed','','385-revision-37','','','2013-03-05 06:54:59','2013-03-05 14:54:59','',385,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/385-revision-37/',0,'revision','',0),(1306,3,'2013-03-05 06:57:09','2013-03-05 14:57:09','It is difficult enough to accept hearing loss when it is your own issue. But when it affects a close friend or family member, it can be even more difficult. You may find yourself in the unenviable position of having to convince your parent, grandparent, sibling, or other relative that it is time to get a hearing exam and facing tremendous resistance to the very idea. So how can you convince someone to get tested?','Dealing with Resistance','','inherit','closed','closed','','460-revision-14','','','2013-03-05 06:57:09','2013-03-05 14:57:09','',460,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/460-revision-14/',0,'revision','',0),(1307,3,'2013-03-06 16:27:16','2013-03-07 00:27:16','','Hearing is Believing','','inherit','closed','closed','','1272-revision-2','','','2013-03-06 16:27:16','2013-03-07 00:27:16','',1272,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/1272-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(1308,3,'2013-03-05 06:59:32','2013-03-05 14:59:32','Your friend or family member may not be aware he or she is having a problem hearing. In fact, you may not be certain they have a problem, but only suspect something may be going on. By learning to recognize the symptoms associated with hearing loss, you can be more confident when speaking to your friend or family member about your concerns, and be equipped with evidence to back up your claims.','Identifying Hearing Loss in Others Checklist','','inherit','closed','closed','','442-revision-10','','','2013-03-05 06:59:32','2013-03-05 14:59:32','',442,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/442-revision-10/',0,'revision','',0),(1309,3,'2013-03-06 16:29:49','2013-03-07 00:29:49','','Hearing Loss Simulator','','inherit','closed','closed','','1274-revision-3','','','2013-03-06 16:29:49','2013-03-07 00:29:49','',1274,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/1274-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(1310,3,'2013-03-06 16:31:54','2013-03-07 00:31:54','','First Steps Toward a Solution','','inherit','closed','closed','','1277-revision-2','','','2013-03-06 16:31:54','2013-03-07 00:31:54','',1277,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/1277-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(1311,3,'2013-03-05 07:01:51','2013-03-05 15:01:51','Don’t assume you have all the information you need to make decisions about your hearing—do the research, talk to hearing care professionals, and learn to separate the myths from reality. Here are five of the more persistent misconceptions about hearing loss:','Misconceptions about Hearing Loss ','','inherit','closed','closed','','479-revision-27','','','2013-03-05 07:01:51','2013-03-05 15:01:51','',479,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/479-revision-27/',0,'revision','',0),(1312,3,'2013-03-05 07:06:06','2013-03-05 15:06:06','One of the most difficult aspects of hearing loss is the lonely solitude that comes with it. It may prove somewhat comforting to know that not only are you far from alone in experiencing hearing loss, but you share this condition with some very prominent people from the worlds of entertainment, music, sports, and history. Here are just a few inspiring examples.','10 Famous People with Hearing Loss','','inherit','closed','closed','','397-revision-20','','','2013-03-05 07:06:06','2013-03-05 15:06:06','',397,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/397-revision-20/',0,'revision','',0),(1313,3,'2013-03-06 16:25:06','2013-03-07 00:25:06','','Personal Stories about Hearing Loss','','inherit','closed','closed','','1270-revision-2','','','2013-03-06 16:25:06','2013-03-07 00:25:06','',1270,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/1270-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(1314,3,'2013-03-05 07:11:46','2013-03-05 15:11:46','Beyond the emotional impact hearing loss has on you is the toll it takes on others.','Hearing Loss & Others','','inherit','closed','closed','','468-revision-20','','','2013-03-05 07:11:46','2013-03-05 15:11:46','',468,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/468-revision-20/',0,'revision','',0),(1315,3,'2013-03-05 07:08:26','2013-03-05 15:08:26','While the downturn in our economy has affected nearly every working-age citizen negatively—either leaving them unable to find a job, change jobs, or receive reasonable cost-of-living salary increases—several studies have shown that those affected by hearing loss have been hit harder than most.','Economic Impact of Hearing Loss','','inherit','closed','closed','','448-revision-17','','','2013-03-05 07:08:26','2013-03-05 15:08:26','',448,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/448-revision-17/',0,'revision','',0),(1316,3,'2013-03-05 07:03:54','2013-03-05 15:03:54','From the moment you were born, you began experiencing your world through your five senses. By seeing, you learned to recognize your father’s smile. By tasting, you learned you preferred peaches to spinach. And by hearing, you were lulled to sleep by your mother’s singing.\r\n\r\nThe reduction or loss of one of your senses has a pronounced effect on your ability to participate in life, and the lives of those you care about. Losing your hearing can be particularly disturbing because it is often associated with aging and ebbing vitality many people are not ready to accept.','Hearing Loss & You','','inherit','closed','closed','','497-revision-13','','','2013-03-05 07:03:54','2013-03-05 15:03:54','',497,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/497-revision-13/',0,'revision','',0),(1317,3,'2013-03-05 09:25:25','2013-03-05 17:25:25','You’ve met with a hearing care professional, had your audiogram, learned which hearing aids will work best for you, and made the decision to move forward. Congratulations! Now it’s time to prepare for your hearing aid fitting. To help alleviate any anxiety you may be feeling, here is what you should expect to go on during this important visit.','What to Expect at Your First Fitting','','inherit','closed','closed','','633-revision-12','','','2013-03-05 09:25:25','2013-03-05 17:25:25','',633,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/633-revision-12/',0,'revision','',0),(1318,3,'2013-03-05 09:14:18','2013-03-05 17:14:18','If you have already scheduled an appointment for your first hearing aid fitting, you are probably wondering what information you should know or bring with you. The more thorough background about your medical history, hearing issues, lifestyle, and other unique needs you can provide, the easier it will be for the hearing aid provider to help you choose and be fitted for the best possible hearing instruments.','Appointment Checklist','','inherit','closed','closed','','597-revision-12','','','2013-03-05 09:14:18','2013-03-05 17:14:18','',597,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/597-revision-12/',0,'revision','',0),(1319,3,'2013-03-05 09:23:42','2013-03-05 17:23:42','Learning to listen with hearing aids takes time and a degree of patience in the beginning. It‘s also important to be realistic and not to expect 100 percent flawless hearing in every situation, especially right away. The key to success is forming an active partnership with your provider, reading all materials provided, and following directions.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nDuring follow up visits, your hearing aid provider will answer any questions that may arise with use, make any technical adjustments or cleaning warranted, and generally help you adapt to and enjoy your hearing instruments. Here is what to expect during these follow up visits.','Follow-Up Visits and Warranties','','inherit','closed','closed','','583-revision-19','','','2013-03-05 09:23:42','2013-03-05 17:23:42','',583,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/583-revision-19/',0,'revision','',0),(1320,3,'2013-03-05 09:09:16','2013-03-05 17:09:16','Your audiogram and your own comments about how well you can hear in a variety of listening environments help determine the optimum setting for your hearing aids. While fitting your hearing aids, your hearing care professional adjusts them by measuring how well you can hear. At your first fitting, you will be taught how to operate your hearing aids and how to hear best in different listening environments. Your hearing care professional will also offer tips for communicating while wearing hearing instruments, encourage you to practice inserting and removing the instruments, and instruct you in cleaning and caring for your hearing aids, as well as proper battery use and storage. You should also expect to schedule an appointment for your first follow up visit about a week later.','10 Things to Ask at Your First Fitting','','inherit','closed','closed','','579-revision-9','','','2013-03-05 09:09:16','2013-03-05 17:09:16','',579,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/579-revision-9/',0,'revision','',0),(1321,3,'2013-02-28 19:15:53','2013-03-01 03:15:53','Hearing aids are a serious, long-term investment. While you will likely need to change them out periodically over the years, good care and maintenance are the keys to keeping your hearing aids in top condition.','Hearing Aid Maintenance','','inherit','closed','closed','','611-revision-10','','','2013-02-28 19:15:53','2013-03-01 03:15:53','',611,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/611-revision-10/',0,'revision','',0),(1322,3,'2013-03-05 11:14:35','2013-03-05 19:14:35','Hearing aids have improved the travel experience for numerous hearing impaired tourists. Instead of straining to hear tour guides, missing boarding announcements, and struggling to negotiate unfamiliar public transportation, hearing aid wearers can enjoy trips without extra hassle and worry. But, it’s important to protect and maintain your hearing aids while traveling, so that they continue to provide the top performance you need while away from home.','Traveling with Hearing Aids','','inherit','closed','closed','','648-revision-9','','','2013-03-05 11:14:35','2013-03-05 19:14:35','',648,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/648-revision-9/',0,'revision','',0),(1323,3,'2013-03-05 11:09:22','2013-03-05 19:09:22','Let’s say you already met with a hearing care professional and determined that hearing aids are right for you. Now you face an array of choices about the type of hearing instruments available. From behind-the-ear (BTE) to in-the-ear (ITE) models, you may be overwhelmed by how many choices you have and unsure which version will suit your lifestyle.','Lifestyle Inventory Checklist','','inherit','closed','closed','','619-revision-15','','','2013-03-05 11:09:22','2013-03-05 19:09:22','',619,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/619-revision-15/',0,'revision','',0),(1324,3,'2013-03-05 11:12:05','2013-03-05 19:12:05','Most digital hearing aids are equipped with options to allow you to hear in a variety of environments. As you change settings throughout the day, you can push a button on your hearing aids to select a program appropriate to your surroundings. Or, if you have more advanced digital hearing aids, they will switch programs automatically based on an analysis of environmental sounds. Your audiologist or other hearing care professional will set up the programs at your fitting and tweak them as necessary during follow-up visits.','Settings for Different Environments','','inherit','closed','closed','','642-revision-8','','','2013-03-05 11:12:05','2013-03-05 19:12:05','',642,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/642-revision-8/',0,'revision','',0),(1325,3,'2013-02-06 22:48:27','2013-02-06 22:48:27','','Our Partners','','inherit','closed','closed','','44-revision-2','','','2013-02-06 22:48:27','2013-02-06 22:48:27','',44,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/44-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(1326,3,'2013-02-20 19:30:01','2013-02-21 03:30:01','','Download the Hearing Aid Guide','','inherit','closed','closed','','39-revision-13','','','2013-02-20 19:30:01','2013-02-21 03:30:01','',39,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/39-revision-13/',0,'revision','',0),(1327,3,'2013-02-28 19:36:41','2013-03-01 03:36:41','If you’ve realized that you or someone you love may be struggling with hearing loss, it’s time to take action. Fill out the form below and a hearing care provider will contact you. Or if you prefer the phone, you can call us at 855-355-9064.','Contact a Hearing Care Provider','','inherit','closed','closed','','37-revision-16','','','2013-02-2