ypes of hearing loss overview, you know that there are several types of hearing loss. There are also many causes.</p>','Causes of Hearing Loss','','inherit','closed','closed','','975-revision-11','','','2013-03-07 10:26:35','2013-03-07 18:26:35','',975,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/975-revision-11/',0,'revision','',0),(1384,3,'2013-03-07 10:26:51','2013-03-07 18:26:51','<p class=\"heading\">If you already read our types of hearing loss overview, you know that there are several types of hearing loss. There are also many causes.</p>','Causes of Hearing Loss','','inherit','closed','closed','','975-revision-12','','','2013-03-07 10:26:51','2013-03-07 18:26:51','',975,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/975-revision-12/',0,'revision','',0),(1385,3,'2013-03-06 16:51:28','2013-03-07 00:51:28','Hearing loss is often a symptom or outcome of other medical conditions, which can be very serious or even life threatening. This is yet another reason that it is so important to recognize the signs of hearing loss and seek treatment from a hearing care professional as soon as possible. More than your hearing may be at stake.\r\n\r\nThe following are a sampling of other illnesses and afflictions linked to hearing loss. A qualified otolaryngologist (ear, nose, and throat doctor or ENT) or certified audiologist can help diagnose these conditions and provide recommendations for treatment.','Related Medical Conditions','','inherit','closed','closed','','976-revision-10','','','2013-03-06 16:51:28','2013-03-07 00:51:28','',976,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/976-revision-10/',0,'revision','',0),(1386,3,'2013-03-07 10:30:04','2013-03-07 18:30:04','<p class=\"heading\">Hearing loss is often a symptom or outcome of other medical conditions, which can be very serious or even life threatening. This is yet another reason that it is so important to recognize the signs of hearing loss and seek treatment from a hearing care professional as soon as possible. More than your hearing may be at stake.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"heading\">The following are a sampling of other illnesses and afflictions linked to hearing loss. A qualified otolaryngologist (ear, nose, and throat doctor or ENT) or certified audiologist can help diagnose these conditions and provide recommendations for treatment.</p>','Related Medical Conditions','','inherit','closed','closed','','976-revision-11','','','2013-03-07 10:30:04','2013-03-07 18:30:04','',976,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/976-revision-11/',0,'revision','',0),(1387,3,'2013-03-06 16:50:02','2013-03-07 00:50:02','Researchers continue to learn more about hearing loss, its causes and contributing factors, and effects. There are ways to reduce the likelihood of losing your hearing in some cases, while others are simply beyond our control.\r\n','10 Things to Know about Hearing Loss','','inherit','closed','closed','','160-revision-30','','','2013-03-06 16:50:02','2013-03-07 00:50:02','',160,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/160-revision-30/',0,'revision','',0),(1388,3,'2013-03-07 10:34:05','2013-03-07 18:34:05','<p class=\"heading\">Researchers continue to learn more about hearing loss, its causes and contributing factors, and effects. There are ways to reduce the likelihood of losing your hearing in some cases, while others are simply beyond our control.</p>','10 Things to Know about Hearing Loss','','inherit','closed','closed','','160-revision-31','','','2013-03-07 10:34:05','2013-03-07 18:34:05','',160,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/160-revision-31/',0,'revision','',0),(1389,1,'2013-03-07 10:35:08','2013-03-07 18:35:08','<p class=\"heading\">Researchers continue to learn more about hearing loss, its causes and contributing factors, and effects. There are ways to reduce the likelihood of losing your hearing in some cases, while others are simply beyond our control.</p>','10 Things to Know about Hearing Loss','','inherit','closed','closed','','160-revision-32','','','2013-03-07 10:35:08','2013-03-07 18:35:08','',160,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/160-revision-32/',0,'revision','',0),(1390,1,'2013-03-07 10:50:34','2013-03-07 18:50:34','<p class=\"heading\">Researchers continue to learn more about hearing loss, its causes and contributing factors, and effects. There are ways to reduce the likelihood of losing your hearing in some cases, while others are simply beyond our control.</p>','10 Things to Know about Hearing Loss','','inherit','closed','closed','','160-revision-33','','','2013-03-07 10:50:34','2013-03-07 18:50:34','',160,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/160-revision-33/',0,'revision','',0),(1391,3,'2013-03-06 16:54:50','2013-03-07 00:54:50','Tinnitus affects up to 50 million people in the United States<a title=\"\" href=\"#_ftn1\">[1]</a>. It is the number one disability suffered by combat veterans and affects at least one in every 10 American adults. Yet very few people, even those who have it, know what it is or what they can do to combat it.\r\n\r\nTinnitus comes from the Latin word <i>tinnire</i> (to ring) and is a perception of sound for which there is no actual external source. You may describe it as ringing in your ears, while to others it sounds like humming, buzzing, or whistling. Tinnitus is a symptom of some kind of damage to your auditory processing system, but is not itself a cause. The most common culprit is the same as for hearing loss — noise exposure. However, sometimes no specific cause can be identified.\r\n<div><br clear=\"all\" />\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"left\" size=\"1\" width=\"33%\" />\r\n\r\n</div>','Tinnitus','','inherit','closed','closed','','10-revision-13','','','2013-03-06 16:54:50','2013-03-07 00:54:50','',10,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/10-revision-13/',0,'revision','',0),(1392,3,'2013-03-07 12:34:22','2013-03-07 20:34:22','<p class=\"heading\">Tinnitus affects up to 50 million people in the United States<a title=\"\" href=\"#_ftn1\">[1]</a>. It is the number one disability suffered by combat veterans and affects at least one in every 10 American adults. Yet very few people, even those who have it, know what it is or what they can do to combat it.</p>\r\n<p class=\"heading\">Tinnitus comes from the Latin word <i>tinnire</i> (to ring) and is a perception of sound for which there is no actual external source. You may describe it as ringing in your ears, while to others it sounds like humming, buzzing, or whistling. Tinnitus is a symptom of some kind of damage to your auditory processing system, but is not itself a cause. The most common culprit is the same as for hearing loss — noise exposure. However, sometimes no specific cause can be identified.</p>\r\n<div><br clear=\"all\" /></p>\r\n<hr align=\"left\" size=\"1\" width=\"33%\" />\r\n</div>','Tinnitus','','inherit','closed','closed','','10-revision-14','','','2013-03-07 12:34:22','2013-03-07 20:34:22','',10,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/10-revision-14/',0,'revision','',0),(1393,3,'2013-03-07 12:35:24','2013-03-07 20:35:24','<p class=\"heading\">Tinnitus affects up to 50 million people in the United States<a title=\"\" href=\"#_ftn1\"><sup>[1]</sup></a>. It is the number one disability suffered by combat veterans and affects at least one in every 10 American adults. Yet very few people, even those who have it, know what it is or what they can do to combat it.</p>\r\n<p class=\"heading\">Tinnitus comes from the Latin word <i>tinnire</i> (to ring) and is a perception of sound for which there is no actual external source. You may describe it as ringing in your ears, while to others it sounds like humming, buzzing, or whistling. Tinnitus is a symptom of some kind of damage to your auditory processing system, but is not itself a cause. The most common culprit is the same as for hearing loss — noise exposure. However, sometimes no specific cause can be identified.</p>','Tinnitus','','inherit','closed','closed','','10-revision-15','','','2013-03-07 12:35:24','2013-03-07 20:35:24','',10,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/10-revision-15/',0,'revision','',0),(1394,3,'2013-03-06 17:06:43','2013-03-07 01:06:43','From the moment you were born, you began experiencing your world through your five senses. By seeing, you learned to recognize your father’s smile. By tasting, you learned you preferred peaches to spinach. And by hearing, you were lulled to sleep by your mother’s singing.\r\n\r\nThe reduction or loss of one of your senses has a pronounced effect on your ability to participate in life, and the lives of those you care about. Losing your hearing can be particularly disturbing because it is often associated with aging and ebbing vitality many people are not ready to accept.','Hearing Loss & You','','inherit','closed','closed','','497-revision-14','','','2013-03-06 17:06:43','2013-03-07 01:06:43','',497,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/497-revision-14/',0,'revision','',0),(1395,3,'2013-03-06 17:06:33','2013-03-07 01:06:33','While the downturn in our economy has affected nearly every working-age citizen negatively—either leaving them unable to find a job, change jobs, or receive reasonable cost-of-living salary increases—several studies have shown that those affected by hearing loss have been hit harder than most.','Economic Impact of Hearing Loss','','inherit','closed','closed','','448-revision-18','','','2013-03-06 17:06:33','2013-03-07 01:06:33','',448,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/448-revision-18/',0,'revision','',0),(1396,3,'2013-03-07 12:46:20','2013-03-07 20:46:20','<p class=\"heading\">While the downturn in our economy has affected nearly every working-age citizen negatively—either leaving them unable to find a job, change jobs, or receive reasonable cost-of-living salary increases—several studies have shown that those affected by hearing loss have been hit harder than most.</p>','Economic Impact of Hearing Loss','','inherit','closed','closed','','448-revision-19','','','2013-03-07 12:46:20','2013-03-07 20:46:20','',448,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/448-revision-19/',0,'revision','',0),(1397,3,'2013-03-06 17:06:22','2013-03-07 01:06:22','Beyond the emotional impact hearing loss has on you is the toll it takes on others.','Hearing Loss & Others','','inherit','closed','closed','','468-revision-21','','','2013-03-06 17:06:22','2013-03-07 01:06:22','',468,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/468-revision-21/',0,'revision','',0),(1398,3,'2013-03-06 17:05:57','2013-03-07 01:05:57','One of the most difficult aspects of hearing loss is the lonely solitude that comes with it. It may prove somewhat comforting to know that not only are you far from alone in experiencing hearing loss, but you share this condition with some very prominent people from the worlds of entertainment, music, sports, and history. Here are just a few inspiring examples.','10 Famous People with Hearing Loss','','inherit','closed','closed','','397-revision-21','','','2013-03-06 17:05:57','2013-03-07 01:05:57','',397,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/397-revision-21/',0,'revision','',0),(1399,3,'2013-03-07 09:53:58','2013-03-07 17:53:58','“Loss of hearing is a medical condition that is associated with physical, emotional, mental and social well-being. Depression, anxiety, emotional instability, phobias, withdrawal, isolation, lessened health status and lessened self-esteem have all been linked to uncorrected hearing loss.”<a title=\"\" href=\"#_ftn1\"><sup>[1]</sup></a>','Getting Friends & Family to Accept Treatment','','inherit','closed','closed','','385-revision-40','','','2013-03-07 09:53:58','2013-03-07 17:53:58','',385,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/385-revision-40/',0,'revision','',0),(1400,3,'2013-03-06 17:04:24','2013-03-07 01:04:24','It is difficult enough to accept hearing loss when it is your own issue. But when it affects a close friend or family member, it can be even more difficult. You may find yourself in the unenviable position of having to convince your parent, grandparent, sibling, or other relative that it is time to get a hearing exam and facing tremendous resistance to the very idea. So how can you convince someone to get tested?','Dealing with Resistance','','inherit','closed','closed','','460-revision-15','','','2013-03-06 17:04:24','2013-03-07 01:04:24','',460,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/460-revision-15/',0,'revision','',0),(1401,3,'2013-03-06 17:04:52','2013-03-07 01:04:52','Your friend or family member may not be aware he or she is having a problem hearing. In fact, you may not be certain they have a problem, but only suspect something may be going on. By learning to recognize the symptoms associated with hearing loss, you can be more confident when speaking to your friend or family member about your concerns, and be equipped with evidence to back up your claims.','Identifying Hearing Loss in Others Checklist','','inherit','closed','closed','','442-revision-11','','','2013-03-06 17:04:52','2013-03-07 01:04:52','',442,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/442-revision-11/',0,'revision','',0),(1402,3,'2013-03-06 17:05:31','2013-03-07 01:05:31','Don’t assume you have all the information you need to make decisions about your hearing—do the research, talk to hearing care professionals, and learn to separate the myths from reality. Here are five of the more persistent misconceptions about hearing loss:','Misconceptions about Hearing Loss','','inherit','closed','closed','','479-revision-28','','','2013-03-06 17:05:31','2013-03-07 01:05:31','',479,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/479-revision-28/',0,'revision','',0),(1403,3,'2013-03-07 14:28:57','2013-03-07 22:28:57','<p class=\"heading\">Don’t assume you have all the information you need to make decisions about your hearing—do the research, talk to hearing care professionals, and learn to separate the myths from reality.</p>','Misconceptions about Hearing Loss','','inherit','closed','closed','','479-revision-29','','','2013-03-07 14:28:57','2013-03-07 22:28:57','',479,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/479-revision-29/',0,'revision','',0),(1404,3,'2013-03-07 14:30:32','2013-03-07 22:30:32','<p class=\"heading\">Don’t assume you have all the information you need to make decisions about your hearing—do the research, talk to hearing care professionals, and learn to separate the myths from reality.</p>\r\n','Misconceptions about Hearing Loss','','inherit','closed','closed','','479-revision-30','','','2013-03-07 14:30:32','2013-03-07 22:30:32','',479,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/479-revision-30/',0,'revision','',0),(1405,3,'2013-03-07 14:31:20','2013-03-07 22:31:20','<p class=\"heading\">Don’t assume you have all the information you need to make decisions about your hearing—do the research, talk to hearing care professionals, and learn to separate the myths from reality.</p>\r\n','Misconceptions about Hearing Loss','','inherit','closed','closed','','479-revision-31','','','2013-03-07 14:31:20','2013-03-07 22:31:20','',479,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/479-revision-31/',0,'revision','',0),(1406,3,'2013-03-07 14:32:23','2013-03-07 22:32:23','<p class=\"heading\">Don’t assume you have all the information you need to make decisions about your hearing—do the research, talk to hearing care professionals, and learn to separate the myths from reality.</p>\r\n','Misconceptions about Hearing Loss','','inherit','closed','closed','','479-revision-32','','','2013-03-07 14:32:23','2013-03-07 22:32:23','',479,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/479-revision-32/',0,'revision','',0),(1407,3,'2013-03-06 17:03:57','2013-03-07 01:03:57','There is no way around it—the best way to treat any condition is to avoid getting it in the first place. Unfortunately, we often don’t have much control over developing hearing loss. A serious illness, an accident, or the aging process can all cause or contribute to the condition regardless of how careful we are to take preventative measures. However, unlike other sources of hearing loss, noise-induced hearing loss (NIHL) can be prevented if you recognize the risks and take reasonable precautions.','Avoiding Hearing Loss','','inherit','closed','closed','','17-revision-20','','','2013-03-06 17:03:57','2013-03-07 01:03:57','',17,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/17-revision-20/',0,'revision','',0),(1408,3,'2013-03-05 07:35:10','2013-03-05 15:35:10','Wondering how hearing aids work? The simplest answer is that hearing aids selectively increase the volume of sounds and filter out noises. They make soft sounds more audible and easily understood, while keeping moderate or loud sounds at a comfortable listening level. This helps hearing in both noisy and quiet situations. While no hearing aid can solve every hearing problem or restore normal hearing, today\'s hearing aids adjust to environmental sounds so you can hear and understand better.','How Hearing Aids Work','','inherit','closed','closed','','21-revision-19','','','2013-03-05 07:35:10','2013-03-05 15:35:10','',21,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/21-revision-19/',0,'revision','',0),(1409,3,'2013-03-07 14:49:03','2013-03-07 22:49:03','<p class=\"heading\">Wondering how hearing aids work? The simplest answer is that hearing aids selectively increase the volume of sounds and filter out noises. They make soft sounds more audible and easily understood, while keeping moderate or loud sounds at a comfortable listening level. This helps hearing in both noisy and quiet situations. While no hearing aid can solve every hearing problem or restore normal hearing, today\'s hearing aids adjust to environmental sounds so you can hear and understand better.</p>','How Hearing Aids Work','','inherit','closed','closed','','21-revision-20','','','2013-03-07 14:49:03','2013-03-07 22:49:03','',21,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/21-revision-20/',0,'revision','',0),(1410,3,'2013-03-06 16:58:09','2013-03-07 00:58:09','Today, hearing aids are sophisticated tiny digital sound systems that come in many different styles and with many advanced features. At their core, all hearing instruments are miniature amplification systems made to fit either in the ear or behind the ear. ITE hearing aids have custom formed ear molds made from acrylic or silicon, or an individual shell, while BTE hearing aids come in their own plastic casing, which in some models is interchangeable.\r\n\r\nHearing aids help you enjoy the beauty of sound, but they also reflect your personality and style. You need to be both physically and emotionally comfortable wearing them. The good news is that modern hearing aids are discreet. Some look like fashion accessories, while others are so light and comfortable that if not for your improved hearing, you would forget you were wearing them.','What is a Hearing Aid?','','inherit','closed','closed','','728-revision-10','','','2013-03-06 16:58:09','2013-03-07 00:58:09','',728,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/728-revision-10/',0,'revision','',0),(1411,3,'2013-03-07 14:51:16','2013-03-07 22:51:16','<p class=\"heading\">Today, hearing aids are sophisticated tiny digital sound systems that come in many different styles and with many advanced features. At their core, all hearing instruments are miniature amplification systems made to fit either in the ear or behind the ear. ITE hearing aids have custom formed ear molds made from acrylic or silicon, or an individual shell, while BTE hearing aids come in their own plastic casing, which in some models is interchangeable.</p>\r\n<p class=\"heading\">Hearing aids help you enjoy the beauty of sound, but they also reflect your personality and style. You need to be both physically and emotionally comfortable wearing them. The good news is that modern hearing aids are discreet. Some look like fashion accessories, while others are so light and comfortable that if not for your improved hearing, you would forget you were wearing them.</p>','What is a Hearing Aid?','','inherit','closed','closed','','728-revision-11','','','2013-03-07 14:51:16','2013-03-07 22:51:16','',728,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/728-revision-11/',0,'revision','',0),(1412,3,'2013-03-06 16:57:57','2013-03-07 00:57:57','Hearing aids have come a long way since their invention. Wearers are no longer confined to clunky, obvious beige or grey devices that issue high-pitched whines at the most inconvenient moments. Today’s technology has led to great advances when it comes to function and style options. Several styles of hearing aids are now available, along with many design and color options. The most common types of hearing aids include in-the-ear (ITE) or behind-the-ear (BTE) devices.','Hearing Aid Types','','inherit','closed','closed','','718-revision-8','','','2013-03-06 16:57:57','2013-03-07 00:57:57','',718,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/718-revision-8/',0,'revision','',0),(1413,3,'2013-03-06 16:57:46','2013-03-07 00:57:46','Hearing aids have come a long way since their inception. The earliest versions from the 19<sup>th</sup> century involved ear trumpets connected to long tubes that directed sound into the ear. Thanks to the efforts of three great inventors, hearing aid technology advanced considerably:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Alexander Graham Bell used a microphone and battery to amplify sound electronically for his new telephone.</li>\r\n	<li>Werner Von Siemens invented the first technology-based solution for hearing loss.</li>\r\n	<li>Thomas Edison invented the carbon transmitter that converted sound into electrical impulses conducted through wires and converted it back again.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHearing aids continued to evolve, using vacuum tubes and then transistors, until entering the modern age of analog, digital, and computers/microchips. Today’s hearing instruments are marvels of technology that continues to advance with each passing year.','Hearing Aid Technology','','inherit','closed','closed','','711-revision-11','','','2013-03-06 16:57:46','2013-03-07 00:57:46','',711,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/711-revision-11/',0,'revision','',0),(1414,3,'2013-03-07 14:57:46','2013-03-07 22:57:46','<p class=\"heading\">Hearing aids have come a long way since their inception. The earliest versions from the 19<sup>th</sup> century involved ear trumpets connected to long tubes that directed sound into the ear. Thanks to the efforts of three great inventors, hearing aid technology advanced considerably:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Alexander Graham Bell used a microphone and battery to amplify sound electronically for his new telephone.</li>\r\n<li>Werner Von Siemens invented the first technology-based solution for hearing loss.</li>\r\n<li>Thomas Edison invented the carbon transmitter that converted sound into electrical impulses conducted through wires and converted it back again.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"heading\">Hearing aids continued to evolve, using vacuum tubes and then transistors, until entering the modern age of analog, digital, and computers/microchips. Today’s hearing instruments are marvels of technology that continues to advance with each passing year.</p>','Hearing Aid Technology','','inherit','closed','closed','','711-revision-12','','','2013-03-07 14:57:46','2013-03-07 22:57:46','',711,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/711-revision-12/',0,'revision','',0),(1415,3,'2013-03-07 14:58:24','2013-03-07 22:58:24','<p class=\"heading\">Hearing aids have come a long way since their inception. The earliest versions from the 19<sup>th</sup> century involved ear trumpets connected to long tubes that directed sound into the ear. Thanks to the efforts of three great inventors, hearing aid technology advanced considerably:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><p class=\"heading\">Alexander Graham Bell used a microphone and battery to amplify sound electronically for his new telephone.</p></li>\r\n<li>Werner Von Siemens invented the first technology-based solution for hearing loss.</li>\r\n<li>Thomas Edison invented the carbon transmitter that converted sound into electrical impulses conducted through wires and converted it back again.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"heading\">Hearing aids continued to evolve, using vacuum tubes and then transistors, until entering the modern age of analog, digital, and computers/microchips. Today’s hearing instruments are marvels of technology that continues to advance with each passing year.</p>','Hearing Aid Technology','','inherit','closed','closed','','711-revision-13','','','2013-03-07 14:58:24','2013-03-07 22:58:24','',711,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/711-revision-13/',0,'revision','',0),(1416,3,'2013-03-07 10:09:19','2013-03-07 18:09:19','<p class=\"heading\">When you see a hearing care professional for diagnosis of your hearing loss, he or she is likely to tell you more than simply, “You have lost some hearing.” Rather, you will probably be told that you have a specific type of hearing loss:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>conductive</li>\r\n	<li>sensorineural</li>\r\n	<li>mixed</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"heading\">Here’s a brief overview of each hearing loss type, its likely causes, and the treatment options usually proposed.</p>','Types of Hearing Loss','','inherit','closed','closed','','210-revision-30','','','2013-03-07 10:09:19','2013-03-07 18:09:19','',210,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/210-revision-30/',0,'revision','',0),(1417,3,'2013-03-07 15:00:47','2013-03-07 23:00:47','<p class=\"heading\">When you see a hearing care professional for diagnosis of your hearing loss, he or she is likely to tell you more than simply, “You have lost some hearing.” Rather, you will probably be told that you have a specific type of hearing loss:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><p class=\"heading\">conductive</p></li>\r\n<li><p class=\"heading\">sensorineural</p></li>\r\n<li><p class=\"heading\">mixed</p></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"heading\">Here’s a brief overview of each hearing loss type, its likely causes, and the treatment options usually proposed.</p>','Types of Hearing Loss','','inherit','closed','closed','','210-revision-31','','','2013-03-07 15:00:47','2013-03-07 23:00:47','',210,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/210-revision-31/',0,'revision','',0),(1418,3,'2013-03-07 15:02:54','2013-03-07 23:02:54','<p class=\"heading\">When you see a hearing care professional for diagnosis of your hearing loss, he or she is likely to tell you more than simply, “You have lost some hearing.” Rather, you will probably be told that you have a specific type of hearing loss:</p>\r\n<ul><p class=\"heading\">\r\n<li>conductive</li>\r\n<li>sensorineural</li>\r\n<li>mixed</p>\r\n</li></p>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"heading\">Here’s a brief overview of each hearing loss type, its likely causes, and the treatment options usually proposed.</p>','Types of Hearing Loss','','inherit','closed','closed','','210-revision-32','','','2013-03-07 15:02:54','2013-03-07 23:02:54','',210,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/210-revision-32/',0,'revision','',0),(1419,3,'2013-03-06 17:18:26','2013-03-07 01:18:26','Here are answers to some of the most commonly asked questions about hearing loss and hearing aids. For answers specific to your concerns, consult a hearing care professional for proper examination and testing.','FAQs','','inherit','closed','closed','','60-revision-24','','','2013-03-06 17:18:26','2013-03-07 01:18:26','',60,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/60-revision-24/',0,'revision','',0),(1420,3,'2013-03-07 15:06:29','2013-03-07 23:06:29','<p class=\"heading\">Here are answers to some of the most commonly asked questions about hearing loss and hearing aids. For answers specific to your concerns, consult a hearing care professional for proper examination and testing.</p>','FAQs','','inherit','closed','closed','','60-revision-25','','','2013-03-07 15:06:29','2013-03-07 23:06:29','',60,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/60-revision-25/',0,'revision','',0),(1421,9,'2013-03-11 11:40:39','2013-03-11 19:40:39','<p>Wondering how to get a friend or loved one to seek treatment for their hearing loss? An audiologist provides suggestions  as to what steps to take in this video.</p>','First Steps Toward a Solution','','inherit','closed','closed','','1277-autosave','','','2013-03-11 11:40:39','2013-03-11 19:40:39','',1277,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/1277-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(1422,8,'2013-03-08 08:46:28','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','closed','closed','','','','','2013-03-08 08:46:28','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://10.2.10.246