m/33-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(1437,3,'2013-03-08 09:03:12','2013-03-08 17:03:12','<p class=\"heading\">Here are answers to some of the most commonly asked questions about hearing loss and hearing aids. For answers specific to your concerns, consult a hearing care professional for proper examination and testing.</p>\r\n','FAQs','','inherit','closed','closed','','60-revision-27','','','2013-03-08 09:03:12','2013-03-08 17:03:12','',60,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/60-revision-27/',0,'revision','',0),(1438,3,'2013-03-06 17:18:19','2013-03-07 01:18:19','If you are ready to find out whether you should get hearing aids or not, you may be wondering, “Where do I find a hearing care professional?” The good news is there are many options available. You should take care to choose one who is readily available, reliable, trustworthy, and offers the most services for your money.','Where to Find a Hearing Care Professional','','inherit','closed','closed','','58-revision-21','','','2013-03-06 17:18:19','2013-03-07 01:18:19','',58,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/58-revision-21/',0,'revision','',0),(1439,3,'2013-03-06 17:18:08','2013-03-07 01:18:08','','Glossary','','inherit','closed','closed','','54-revision-11','','','2013-03-06 17:18:08','2013-03-07 01:18:08','',54,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/54-revision-11/',0,'revision','',0),(1440,3,'2013-03-06 17:16:40','2013-03-07 01:16:40','Most digital hearing aids are equipped with options to allow you to hear in a variety of environments. As you change settings throughout the day, you can push a button on your hearing aids to select a program appropriate to your surroundings. Or, if you have more advanced digital hearing aids, they will switch programs automatically based on an analysis of environmental sounds. Your audiologist or other hearing care professional will set up the programs at your fitting and tweak them as necessary during follow-up visits.','Settings for Different Environments','','inherit','closed','closed','','642-revision-9','','','2013-03-06 17:16:40','2013-03-07 01:16:40','',642,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/642-revision-9/',0,'revision','',0),(1441,3,'2013-03-06 17:16:31','2013-03-07 01:16:31','Let’s say you already met with a hearing care professional and determined that hearing aids are right for you. Now you face an array of choices about the type of hearing instruments available. From behind-the-ear (BTE) to in-the-ear (ITE) models, you may be overwhelmed by how many choices you have and unsure which version will suit your lifestyle.','Lifestyle Inventory Checklist','','inherit','closed','closed','','619-revision-16','','','2013-03-06 17:16:31','2013-03-07 01:16:31','',619,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/619-revision-16/',0,'revision','',0),(1442,3,'2013-03-08 10:10:28','2013-03-08 18:10:28','<p class=\"heading\">Let’s say you already met with a hearing care professional and determined that hearing aids are right for you. Now you face an array of choices about the type of hearing instruments available. From behind-the-ear (BTE) to in-the-ear (ITE) models, you may be overwhelmed by how many choices you have and unsure which version will suit your lifestyle.</p>','Lifestyle Inventory Checklist','','inherit','closed','closed','','619-revision-17','','','2013-03-08 10:10:28','2013-03-08 18:10:28','',619,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/619-revision-17/',0,'revision','',0),(1443,3,'2013-03-06 17:16:20','2013-03-07 01:16:20','Hearing aids have improved the travel experience for numerous hearing impaired tourists. Instead of straining to hear tour guides, missing boarding announcements, and struggling to negotiate unfamiliar public transportation, hearing aid wearers can enjoy trips without extra hassle and worry. But, it’s important to protect and maintain your hearing aids while traveling, so that they continue to provide the top performance you need while away from home.','Traveling with Hearing Aids','','inherit','closed','closed','','648-revision-10','','','2013-03-06 17:16:20','2013-03-07 01:16:20','',648,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/648-revision-10/',0,'revision','',0),(1444,3,'2013-03-06 17:16:06','2013-03-07 01:16:06','Hearing aids are a serious, long-term investment. While you will likely need to change them out periodically over the years, good care and maintenance are the keys to keeping your hearing aids in top condition.','Hearing Aid Maintenance','','inherit','closed','closed','','611-revision-11','','','2013-03-06 17:16:06','2013-03-07 01:16:06','',611,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/611-revision-11/',0,'revision','',0),(1445,3,'2013-03-05 11:06:27','2013-03-05 19:06:27','Hearing aids have evolved from uncomfortable and unsightly devices to sophisticated, stylish, high-tech instruments with options to compensate for almost every type of hearing impairment. Inconspicuous, yet powerful and versatile, they can do much more than simply make sounds louder.','The Hearing Aid Experience ','','inherit','closed','closed','','31-revision-13','','','2013-03-05 11:06:27','2013-03-05 19:06:27','',31,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/31-revision-13/',0,'revision','',0),(1446,3,'2013-03-06 17:15:38','2013-03-07 01:15:38','Your audiogram and your own comments about how well you can hear in a variety of listening environments help determine the optimum setting for your hearing aids. While fitting your hearing aids, your hearing care professional adjusts them by measuring how well you can hear. At your first fitting, you will be taught how to operate your hearing aids and how to hear best in different listening environments. Your hearing care professional will also offer tips for communicating while wearing hearing instruments, encourage you to practice inserting and removing the instruments, and instruct you in cleaning and caring for your hearing aids, as well as proper battery use and storage. You should also expect to schedule an appointment for your first follow up visit about a week later.','10 Things to Ask at Your First Fitting','','inherit','closed','closed','','579-revision-10','','','2013-03-06 17:15:38','2013-03-07 01:15:38','',579,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/579-revision-10/',0,'revision','',0),(1447,3,'2013-03-08 10:27:59','2013-03-08 18:27:59','<p class=\"heading\">Your audiogram and your own comments about how well you can hear in a variety of listening environments help determine the optimum setting for your hearing aids. While fitting your hearing aids, your hearing care professional adjusts them by measuring how well you can hear. At your first fitting, you will be taught how to operate your hearing aids and how to hear best in different listening environments. Your hearing care professional will also offer tips for communicating while wearing hearing instruments, encourage you to practice inserting and removing the instruments, and instruct you in cleaning and caring for your hearing aids, as well as proper battery use and storage. You should also expect to schedule an appointment for your first follow up visit about a week later.</p>','10 Things to Ask at Your First Fitting','','inherit','closed','closed','','579-revision-11','','','2013-03-08 10:27:59','2013-03-08 18:27:59','',579,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/579-revision-11/',0,'revision','',0),(1448,3,'2013-03-06 17:15:27','2013-03-07 01:15:27','Learning to listen with hearing aids takes time and a degree of patience in the beginning. It‘s also important to be realistic and not to expect 100 percent flawless hearing in every situation, especially right away. The key to success is forming an active partnership with your provider, reading all materials provided, and following directions.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nDuring follow up visits, your hearing aid provider will answer any questions that may arise with use, make any technical adjustments or cleaning warranted, and generally help you adapt to and enjoy your hearing instruments. Here is what to expect during these follow up visits.','Follow-Up Visits and Warranties','','inherit','closed','closed','','583-revision-20','','','2013-03-06 17:15:27','2013-03-07 01:15:27','',583,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/583-revision-20/',0,'revision','',0),(1449,3,'2013-03-08 10:30:28','2013-03-08 18:30:28','<p class=\"heading\">Learning to listen with hearing aids takes time and a degree of patience in the beginning. It‘s also important to be realistic and not to expect 100 percent flawless hearing in every situation, especially right away. The key to success is forming an active partnership with your provider, reading all materials provided, and following directions.</p>\r\n<p>During follow up visits, your hearing aid provider will answer any questions that may arise with use, make any technical adjustments or cleaning warranted, and generally help you adapt to and enjoy your hearing instruments. Here is what to expect during these follow up visits.</p>','Follow-Up Visits and Warranties','','inherit','closed','closed','','583-revision-21','','','2013-03-08 10:30:28','2013-03-08 18:30:28','',583,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/583-revision-21/',0,'revision','',0),(1450,3,'2013-03-06 17:15:14','2013-03-07 01:15:14','If you have already scheduled an appointment for your first hearing aid fitting, you are probably wondering what information you should know or bring with you. The more thorough background about your medical history, hearing issues, lifestyle, and other unique needs you can provide, the easier it will be for the hearing aid provider to help you choose and be fitted for the best possible hearing instruments.','Appointment Checklist','','inherit','closed','closed','','597-revision-13','','','2013-03-06 17:15:14','2013-03-07 01:15:14','',597,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/597-revision-13/',0,'revision','',0),(1451,3,'2013-03-06 17:08:24','2013-03-07 01:08:24','You’ve met with a hearing care professional, had your audiogram, learned which hearing aids will work best for you, and made the decision to move forward. Congratulations! Now it’s time to prepare for your hearing aid fitting. To help alleviate any anxiety you may be feeling, here is what you should expect to go on during this important visit.','What to Expect at Your First Fitting','','inherit','closed','closed','','633-revision-13','','','2013-03-06 17:08:24','2013-03-07 01:08:24','',633,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/633-revision-13/',0,'revision','',0),(1452,3,'2013-03-06 16:57:34','2013-03-07 00:57:34','Hearing aid technology continues to evolve at an impressive rate. You may not be aware of all the innovations that have made hearing aids true digital marvels, enabling wearers to hear in all kinds of environments as well as — or sometimes better than — people with natural hearing. Here are ten examples of advances in hearing aid technology to consider when evaluating how hearing aids could enhance the way you experience life.','10 Things You Didn’t Know About Hearing Aid Technology','','inherit','closed','closed','','744-revision-17','','','2013-03-06 16:57:34','2013-03-07 00:57:34','',744,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/744-revision-17/',0,'revision','',0),(1453,3,'2013-03-08 10:39:49','2013-03-08 18:39:49','<p class=\"heading\">Hearing aid technology continues to evolve at an impressive rate. You may not be aware of all the innovations that have made hearing aids true digital marvels, enabling wearers to hear in all kinds of environments as well as — or sometimes better than — people with natural hearing. Here are ten examples of advances in hearing aid technology to consider when evaluating how hearing aids could enhance the way you experience life.</p>','10 Things You Didn’t Know About Hearing Aid Technology','','inherit','closed','closed','','744-revision-18','','','2013-03-08 10:39:49','2013-03-08 18:39:49','',744,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/744-revision-18/',0,'revision','',0),(1454,3,'2013-03-08 10:40:54','2013-03-08 18:40:54','<p class=\"heading\">Hearing aid technology continues to evolve at an impressive rate. You may not be aware of all the innovations that have made hearing aids true digital marvels, enabling wearers to hear in all kinds of environments as well as — or sometimes better than — people with natural hearing.</p>\r\n','10 Things You Didn’t Know About Hearing Aid Technology','','inherit','closed','closed','','744-revision-19','','','2013-03-08 10:40:54','2013-03-08 18:40:54','',744,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/744-revision-19/',0,'revision','',0),(1455,3,'2013-03-06 16:58:47','2013-03-07 00:58:47','Hearing aids are available from most hearing care professionals at their clinics or offices. However, if you are looking for separate providers, we have some other options for you to investigate.','Where to Buy Hearing Aids','','inherit','closed','closed','','739-revision-7','','','2013-03-06 16:58:47','2013-03-07 00:58:47','',739,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/739-revision-7/',0,'revision','',0),(1456,3,'2013-03-06 16:58:59','2013-03-07 00:58:59','Just like MP3 players and other electronic devices, hearing aids have accessories to keep them clean, functioning optimally, and expand their capabilities. Not sure what’s available or what you need? Here is an overview of several accessories you may want to consider.','Hearing Aid Accessories','','inherit','closed','closed','','691-revision-15','','','2013-03-06 16:58:59','2013-03-07 00:58:59','',691,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/691-revision-15/',0,'revision','',0),(1457,3,'2013-03-08 10:43:58','2013-03-08 18:43:58','<p class=\"heading\">Just like MP3 players and other electronic devices, hearing aids have accessories to keep them clean, functioning optimally, and expand their capabilities. Not sure what’s available or what you need? Here is an overview of several accessories you may want to consider.</p>','Hearing Aid Accessories','','inherit','closed','closed','','691-revision-16','','','2013-03-08 10:43:58','2013-03-08 18:43:58','',691,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/691-revision-16/',0,'revision','',0),(1458,3,'2013-03-06 16:59:14','2013-03-07 00:59:14','Before giving an answer to this, it’s important to first clarify the difference between <i>waterproof </i>and <i>water-resistant</i>. While many people use these interchangeably, the reality is they mean very different things. Mistaking <i>–resistant</i> for <i>–proof</i> could cost you a very pricey pair of hearing aids.','Are Hearing Aids Waterproof?','','inherit','closed','closed','','704-revision-11','','','2013-03-06 16:59:14','2013-03-07 00:59:14','',704,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/704-revision-11/',0,'revision','',0),(1459,3,'2013-03-06 16:59:24','2013-03-07 00:59:24','Besides hearing aids, there are many devices available to assist you if you are hearing impaired. Thanks to continuing advances in technology intended to make the lives of those with special needs easier, a slew of items are available that can do everything from alert you that your baby is crying to make it easier to listen to a teacher’s presentation in the classroom. The following are just a few innovations of which you should be aware.','Related Products','','inherit','closed','closed','','734-revision-7','','','2013-03-06 16:59:24','2013-03-07 00:59:24','',734,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/734-revision-7/',0,'revision','',0),(1460,9,'2013-03-07 09:31:21','2013-03-07 17:31:21','<p class=\"heading\">To understand hearing loss, it helps to know the basic mechanics of how we hear. Our ears, when working properly, are sophisticated organs capable of processing sounds from the scarcely audible to extremely loud. Our ears can assess volume and how close or far away sounds are and identify where sounds originate with a great deal of accuracy. The following explains how this deceptively simple process works.</p>','How We Hear','','inherit','closed','closed','','6-revision-26','','','2013-03-07 09:31:21','2013-03-07 17:31:21','',6,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/6-revision-26/',0,'revision','',0),(1461,3,'2013-03-06 16:59:39','2013-03-07 00:59:39','Upon the introduction of cell phones, people with hearing loss were faced with yet another challenge — how to take advantage of 