ile many people use these interchangeably, the reality is they mean very different things. Mistaking <i>–resistant</i> for <i>–proof</i> could cost you a very pricey pair of hearing aids.</p>\r\n','Are Hearing Aids Waterproof?','','inherit','closed','closed','','704-revision-13','','','2013-03-08 12:51:49','2013-03-08 20:51:49','',704,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/704-revision-13/',0,'revision','',0),(1486,3,'2013-03-08 12:52:19','2013-03-08 20:52:19','<p class=\"heading\">Before giving an answer to this, it’s important to first clarify the difference between <i>waterproof </i>and <i>water-resistant</i>. While many people use these interchangeably, the reality is they mean very different things. Mistaking <i>–resistant</i> for <i>–proof</i> could cost you a very pricey pair of hearing aids.</p>\r\n','Are Hearing Aids Waterproof?','','inherit','closed','closed','','704-revision-14','','','2013-03-08 12:52:19','2013-03-08 20:52:19','',704,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/704-revision-14/',0,'revision','',0),(1487,3,'2013-03-08 10:44:25','2013-03-08 18:44:25','<p class=\"heading\">Just like MP3 players and other electronic devices, hearing aids have accessories to keep them clean, functioning optimally, and expand their capabilities. Not sure what’s available or what you need? Here is an overview of several accessories you may want to consider.</p>\r\n','Hearing Aid Accessories','','inherit','closed','closed','','691-revision-17','','','2013-03-08 10:44:25','2013-03-08 18:44:25','',691,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/691-revision-17/',0,'revision','',0),(1488,3,'2013-03-08 10:41:07','2013-03-08 18:41:07','<p class=\"heading\">Hearing aid technology continues to evolve at an impressive rate. You may not be aware of all the innovations that have made hearing aids true digital marvels, enabling wearers to hear in all kinds of environments as well as — or sometimes better than — people with natural hearing.</p>\r\n','10 Things You Didn’t Know About Hearing Aid Technology','','inherit','closed','closed','','744-revision-20','','','2013-03-08 10:41:07','2013-03-08 18:41:07','',744,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/744-revision-20/',0,'revision','',0),(1489,3,'2013-03-08 13:03:11','2013-03-08 21:03:11','<p class=\"heading\">Hearing aid technology continues to evolve at an impressive rate. You may not be aware of all the innovations that have made hearing aids true digital marvels, enabling wearers to hear in all kinds of environments as well as — or sometimes better than — people with natural hearing.</p>\r\n','10 Things You Didn’t Know About Hearing Aid Technology','','inherit','closed','closed','','744-revision-21','','','2013-03-08 13:03:11','2013-03-08 21:03:11','',744,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/744-revision-21/',0,'revision','',0),(1490,3,'2013-03-08 13:03:51','2013-03-08 21:03:51','<p class=\"heading\">Hearing aid technology continues to evolve at an impressive rate. You may not be aware of all the innovations that have made hearing aids true digital marvels, enabling wearers to hear in all kinds of environments as well as — or sometimes better than — people with natural hearing.</p>\r\n','10 Things You Didn’t Know About Hearing Aid Technology','','inherit','closed','closed','','744-revision-22','','','2013-03-08 13:03:51','2013-03-08 21:03:51','',744,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/744-revision-22/',0,'revision','',0),(1491,3,'2013-03-07 14:59:01','2013-03-07 22:59:01','<p class=\"heading\">Hearing aids have come a long way since their inception. The earliest versions from the 19<sup>th</sup> century involved ear trumpets connected to long tubes that directed sound into the ear. Thanks to the efforts of three great inventors, hearing aid technology advanced considerably:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p class=\"heading\">Alexander Graham Bell used a microphone and battery to amplify sound electronically for his new telephone.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><p class=\"heading\">Werner Von Siemens invented the first technology-based solution for hearing loss.</p></li>\r\n<li><p class=\"heading\">Thomas Edison invented the carbon transmitter that converted sound into electrical impulses conducted through wires and converted it back again.</p></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"heading\">Hearing aids continued to evolve, using vacuum tubes and then transistors, until entering the modern age of analog, digital, and computers/microchips. Today’s hearing instruments are marvels of technology that continues to advance with each passing year.</p>','Hearing Aid Technology','','inherit','closed','closed','','711-revision-14','','','2013-03-07 14:59:01','2013-03-07 22:59:01','',711,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/711-revision-14/',0,'revision','',0),(1492,3,'2013-03-08 13:09:56','2013-03-08 21:09:56','<p class=\"heading\">Hearing aids have come a long way since their inception. </p.>','Hearing Aid Technology','','inherit','closed','closed','','711-revision-15','','','2013-03-08 13:09:56','2013-03-08 21:09:56','',711,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/711-revision-15/',0,'revision','',0),(1493,3,'2013-03-08 13:10:08','2013-03-08 21:10:08','<p class=\"heading\">Hearing aids have come a long way since their inception. </p.>\r\n','Hearing Aid Technology','','inherit','closed','closed','','711-revision-16','','','2013-03-08 13:10:08','2013-03-08 21:10:08','',711,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/711-revision-16/',0,'revision','',0),(1494,3,'2013-03-07 14:54:08','2013-03-07 22:54:08','<p class=\"heading\">Today, hearing aids are sophisticated tiny digital sound systems that come in many different styles and with many advanced features. At their core, all hearing instruments are miniature amplification systems made to fit either in the ear or behind the ear. ITE hearing aids have custom formed ear molds made from acrylic or silicon, or an individual shell, while BTE hearing aids come in their own plastic casing, which in some models is interchangeable.</p>\r\n<p class=\"heading\">Hearing aids help you enjoy the beauty of sound, but they also reflect your personality and style. You need to be both physically and emotionally comfortable wearing them. The good news is that modern hearing aids are discreet. Some look like fashion accessories, while others are so light and comfortable that if not for your improved hearing, you would forget you were wearing them.</p>\r\n','What is a Hearing Aid?','','inherit','closed','closed','','728-revision-12','','','2013-03-07 14:54:08','2013-03-07 22:54:08','',728,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/728-revision-12/',0,'revision','',0),(1495,3,'2013-03-08 13:17:22','2013-03-08 21:17:22','<p class=\"heading\">Today, hearing aids are sophisticated tiny digital sound systems that come in many different styles and with many advanced features. At their core, all hearing instruments are miniature amplification systems made to fit either in the ear or behind the ear. ITE hearing aids have custom formed ear molds made from acrylic or silicon, or an individual shell, while BTE hearing aids come in their own plastic casing, which in some models is interchangeable.</p>\r\n\r\n','What is a Hearing Aid?','','inherit','closed','closed','','728-revision-13','','','2013-03-08 13:17:22','2013-03-08 21:17:22','',728,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/728-revision-13/',0,'revision','',0),(1496,3,'2013-03-06 17:26:08','2013-03-07 01:26:08','In this section, you will learn about hearing aids, related accessories and the technology that makes everything work, along with where you can learn more about hearing aids and  purchase them.','Hearing Aids 101','','inherit','closed','closed','','19-revision-7','','','2013-03-06 17:26:08','2013-03-07 01:26:08','',19,'http://10.2.10.246/ha.com/19-revision-7/',0,'revision','',0),(1497,3,'2013-03-08 13:20:26','2013-03-08 21:20:26','<p>In this section, you will learn about hearing aids, related accessories and the technology that makes everything work, along with where you can learn more about hearing aids and  purchase them.</p>\r\n','Hearing Aids 101','','inherit','closed','closed','','19-revision-8','',''